title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter together.
Mix well.
Make into balls.
Place in refrigerator until cold.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax together in double boiler.
Put toothpicks in balls.
Dip in chocolate.
Let stand on wax paper until cool.

title: fantasia
directions: Process 1st five ingredients.
Serve on cantaloupe balls.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients; sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add vanilla (add 1 cup nuts, dates, raisins or currants).
Fill 2 greased and floured loaf pans half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Smash with a sugar coated glass. Bake 350 degrees until not shiny. Do not let cookies get brown.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and then cover all pretzels. Bake at 200° for 2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to package directions, then add to softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
(Save.)

title: sugar pickles
directions: Wash and place whole cucumbers in glossy stone jar.
Put salt in 1 gallon boiled water.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand for 24 hours.
Pour off brine; add powdered alum to 1 gallon hot water. Let stand 24 hours.
Pour off water.
Add 1 gallon hot clear water and let stand 24 hours.
Pour off water.
Boil 1 gallon of vinegar with spices.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 9 days.
Remove cucumbers from vinegar.
Slice in round slices.
Place in jars; alternate layer of cucumbers with layers of sugar.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and grated German sweet chocolate on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Reserve 2 tablespoons grated chocolate for glaze.
Add remaining grated chocolate to mixture.
When thoroughly mixed, stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
While hot, turn cake onto platter and sprinkle with a mixture of powdered sugar and grated chocolate.

title: scandinavian bar cookies
directions: Mix, then pat with your hands into a 9x13-inch baking pan until about 1/2 inch thick.
Bake until light brown...about 10 minutes at 375°.

title: upside-down pumpkin cake
directions: Mix pumpkin as directed on can.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture; pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and add pecans.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes more.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into size balls you prefer and roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate or freeze for future use.

title: roast beef with mushroom gravy
directions: Season roast on both sides.
Pour mushroom soup, onion soup and water over roast.
Cook on low in crock-pot for 8 hours or in conventional oven at 350° until meat is tender.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Combine these two mixtures and add 1 cup coconut, diced apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 20 minute one pan turkey feast
directions: Brown turkey meatballs in frying pan.
Drain.
Replace meatballs into pan.
Mix other ingredients and place on top meatballs.
Cover and steam for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cherry upside-down cake
directions: Mix cherries, melted butter and brown sugar.
Place cherry mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour cake batter over cherries.
Bake at 350°.
Test cake for doneness.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine in microwave.
Combine melted margarine with the flour and chopped pecans.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Fry sausage; remove grease and mix all together. Roll into little balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken tidbits
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Melt margarine.
Dip chicken in margarine and then in bread crumb mix.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and soda and stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in hot water, quick oats, nuts and chocolate chips and mix well.

title: great friday night meal
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Brown ground beef and mix with can of Manwich.

title: joyce's carrots
directions: Parboil carrots in salted water.
Drain and slice.
Place in small casserole.

title: tangy barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours. Grill chicken over medium coals for 55 to 60 minutes or until done, turning and basting with marinade every 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Mix and spread in large Pyrex dish.
Press with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let it cool.

title: lump crab cakes
directions: Pick over crab meat.
Dice red pepper and celery; place in bowl with crab meat.
Grate onion; add to bowl.
Add eggs, bread crumbs, mustard, Worcestershire, mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce; mix well.
Shape meat into patties; cook in hot butter and oil. Let brown on both sides; drain on paper towels.
Squeeze some lemon juice on crab cakes.

title: amy's fresh orange fruit dip
directions: Combine condensed milk, orange juice and grated orange peel. Cover dip and chill well.
Serve with slices of your favorite fresh fruit.

title: texas chili(bowl of red)
directions: Slightly toast cumin seed in a skillet (preferably cast-iron); crush slightly.
If you use ground cumin, omit this step.
Saute onions and garlic in perhaps 1/4 cup vegetable oil until transparent.
Remove.
In the same skillet, saute the meat in a little more oil and cook and stir until the meat is sort of an even gray all over. Add enough water to cover and the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer some 30 minutes.
Add salt to taste. Simmer another 45 minutes and thicken with flour or cracker meal which has been lightly browned
and made into a thick paste with water. Don't overbrown, it will be bitter.

title: linda's apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour. Stir with a fork until well mixed.
Add apples to this mixture a little at a time, tossing well to coat apples.
Spoon filling into pie crust; add chipped butter over top.
Set aside.

title: nacho dip
directions: Use 10-inch pie plate.
Layer beans, tomatoes, chilies and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle scallions on top. Spread sour cream over top of dip.
In center, spread guacamole dip.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve with chips.

title: cheesy delights
directions: Soften butter to room temperature and mix with cheese.
Add flour, pecans and seasonings.
Mix well.
Make small patties and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt the margarine
and
blend	with stuffing mix.
Put half of the stuffing mix in bottom of casserole.
Add chicken. Mix chicken soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over	chicken
soup
and
broth.
Put
remaining stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook first five ingredients until mixture spins a thread when dropped from tip of spoon.
Remove from fire and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased pan.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cinnamon sour cream coffee cake(student favorite)
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix the dry ingredients into the creamed margarine, etc.
Add sour cream.
Place batter into a tube pan.
Sprinkle with topping of sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mamaw's egg custard
directions: Beat (on low speed) with mixer until combined.
Pour into pie shell (homemade is best).
Bake in preheated 350° oven until firm and brown.
Add meringue and bake if desired.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Slowly add boiling water; stir constantly to avoid lumps.
Simmer while stirring, about 5 minutes or until clear and thickened.
Remove; stir in rest of ingredients.
Serve hot on Cottage Pudding, Custard, Bread Pudding, Dutch Apple Cake, Applesauce Cake or any other cake you prefer.
Makes 2 cups.

title: honey cake (honigkuchen)
directions: In a large bowl place flour, baking powder, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves; stir until blended.
Bring honey and oleo to boil; remove from heat, keep stirring until lukewarm.
Pour over flour mixture; add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Divide evenly into greased and floured loaf pans (9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inches).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 60 minutes.
Set pans on cake rack for 15 minutes; loosen around edges and place on platters.

title: western chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in covered baking dish.
Place 1 slice cheese over each chicken breast.
Combine pineapple and barbecue sauce. Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, flour, melted butter, salt and red pepper in large bowl; mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Shape into quarter-size circles on lightly greased baking sheet and top with pecan halves or leave plain.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until slightly brown around edges.
Yields 60 servings.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Place bacon in a deep 3-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave at High for 3 minutes.
Drain off drippings, reserving 2 tablespoons in casserole.
Add potatoes and onion.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Set clams aside.
Stir clam liquid into potato mixture.
Microwave at High for 7 to 9 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring after 4 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and salt in large skillet just until pink is gone and onion is clear.
Add the next 5 ingredients; heat thoroughly.
In large baking dish, make alternate layers of chips, meat mixture and cheese, ending with a layer of chips and topping with cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.
This is a large recipe; may be frozen.

title: green yellow beans(how to freeze)
directions: Wash beans; snip the ends off, break up or cut beans to the size of your liking. Boil them about 3 to 5 minutes. Rinse in cool/cold water, then bag in quart size bags.

title: cinnamon chip muffins
directions: Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake 12 minutes at 400 degrees.
Serve warm with powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.
Refrigerates well.

title: venison, elk or beef bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake 4 hours at 275°.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Put berries in oblong type baking dish, approximately 6 x 11-inch.
Cover with pineapple.
Pour on dry cake mix and scatter nuts over top.
Melt butter and drizzle over all.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers and steam shells for about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, using only 1/2 can of soup.
Mix well. Fill peppers with stuffing.
Place in shallow baking pan and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour remaining soup over peppers.
Return to oven and continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: heath bar sauce for ice cream
directions: Mix together in saucepan all ingredients except candy.
Cook to a boil and boil for one minute.
Stir in candy.
Remove from heat and let it melt.
When mixture cools and thickens, spoon over ice cream.
Good!

title: spinach pie
directions: Prick pie crust with fork.
Bake pie crust at 400° for 8 minutes.
Layer 1/2 spinach, cheese and onion.
Repeat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over spinach.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° and bake until firm, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring gently.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa. Add shortening, egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir to blend.
After blending by stirring, use mixer and beat thoroughly for 1 minute. Return sauce to heat and bring to a boil.
Drop dumplings into sauce.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt butterscotch in double boiler.
Put in noodles and cover them.
Pour in peanuts.
Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Melt cheese in large pan.
Add Hormel chili, hamburger, tomato sauce and jalapeno peppers to taste.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Microwave or cook broccoli; drain well.
Combine all ingredients.
Press into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: apricot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, oil and nectar.
Add eggs; beat well after each egg.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Remove from pan and ice with glaze.

title: roger's spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in baking dish and melt in oven.
Remove.
In large bowl, beat eggs well.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Add cheese, onion and spinach.
Mix well.
Spoon into baking dish and level off. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool 45 minutes.
Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: In a saucepan, heat cranberry juice to boiling.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill in mold or square pan (9-inch) until set.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Salt chicken and boil until tender. Let cool. Chop fine and mix with mayonnaise, Thousand Island dressing, pickles and boiled eggs.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Put chops in a shallow baking dish.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade cheesecake
directions: Mix milk and sour cream together; get cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix this together; blend in dry pudding mix.
Pour all these ingredients in a graham cracker crust.
Let chill about 1 hour before serving.
Great for company dinner.

title: barbecued chicken(contains 5 g fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Skin the chicken.
Place the chicken "skin" side down in baking pan.
Baste the chicken liberally with barbecue sauce and place in oven.
Bake 20 minutes, basting halfway through, then turn the chicken over and bake another 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.

title: lite rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until beginning to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Pour into serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: holiday jello salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Set in refrigerator.
Mix all fruit and pecan pieces together.
When jello starts to thicken, stir in fruit mixture.
Spoon in cottage cheese.
Just below surface of jello, place in refrigerator overnight.

title: baked eggs "fredric"
directions: Select either "Teflon" or regular muffin pan (spray with Pam). Place approximately 1/4 slice of ham, etc. in bottom of each muffin well.
Line side of well with bacon.
Crack eggs into center of each well (don't break yolks!).
Add light touch of garlic salt to top of egg.
Top with 1/4 slice of cheese and chopped scallions. Bake at 375° approximately 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve whole.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: gluten whole wheat bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water and set aside.
Heat milk and add brown sugar, oil, yeast mixture and soda.
Pour all at once over dry ingredients (wheat flour, gluten flour, salt and wheat germ). Stir until well mixed.
If too soft, add a little more wheat flour. Pour onto board with whole wheat flour and knead until it is elastic.
Set into oiled bowl and turn dough over in the bowl so top has been oiled.
Cover, let rise.
When double in size, shape into loaves and place into well-greased pans.
Let rise until double and bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal salad
directions: Bring pineapple and Sugar
Twin to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool
completely.
Mix
buttermilk and Cool Whip. Add to cooled mixture of pineapple and Sugar Twin.
Stir well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator and let it get firm.

title: zucchini-apple bread
directions: Combine first 6 dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugars, oil and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in zucchini, apple and nuts.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine thawed broccoli with all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with 1/4 cup cracker crumbs mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter, or can use crushed potato chips.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, vanilla, eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix wet and dry ingredients; add apples and nuts.
Batter will be very thick.
Pour into 10 x 13 greased pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
This cake needs no icing.

title: tomato honey(best and most versatile preserves)
directions: Let the tomatoes stand in boiling water until the skins slip off.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain the syrup and boil until fairly thick, then add tomatoes to lemons and ginger.
Cook until tomatoes have a translucent look and the syrup is the consistency of honey.
Cool!
Fill jelly jars and store.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in a covered dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Uncover and cover the top with chow mein noodles and bake, uncovered, for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter; mix with cracker crumbs.
Press in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or bowl.
Beat together until fluffy, eggs, oleo or butter and powdered sugar.
Spread over crumbs in pan or bowl. Add a layer of pineapple, sliced banana and a layer of Cool Whip. Top with nuts and cherries (optional).

title: chocolate fudge pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except frosting.
Blend well. Put in a Bundt cake pan.
Cook at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Then frost with Chocolate Fudge frosting.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water; dissolve.
Pour boiling water over shortening in blender.
Cover and process at stir until blended.
Remove feeder cap.
Add sugar, salt and egg; continue to process until thoroughly blended.
Add yeast mixture and process until thoroughly mixed.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Then add flavorings.
Pour into a large greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° until done.
This makes a large cake so cannot be baked in a Bundt pan.
For a moister cake, cover while still hot with cake cover, foil, etc.

title: canning peppers
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Cut up your peppers in rings or slice them.
Put in jars and cover with syrup and add 1 tablespoon oil to each quart of peppers; seal.
Do not cold pack.
Very crisp.

title: texas tortilla soup
directions: Cut tortillas in narrow strips with scissors and set aside to dry.
Heat oil in saute pan.

Cook garlic clove in oil and remove. Brown tortilla strips in oil and add tomato puree, onion, parsley, chili powder, bay leaf, chicken stock and chicken.	Simmer 15 minutes or until tortilla strips are soft.	Sprinkle grated cheese on top and garnish with tortilla strips and avocado slices.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, soup and sour cream in a bowl.
Melt margarine and mix with dried cornbread.
Combine cornbread (except for 1 cup) with squash mixture and mix well.

title: breakfast sweet rolls
directions: Night before, place frozen rolls in a Bundt pan.
Melt margarine and pour over top of rolls.
Sprinkle other ingredients over top of rolls.
Cover and let rise overnight at room temperature.
Bake in morning at 350° until brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together for 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold in 1 package
of
frozen coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: congealed salad
directions: Put pineapple and juice and jello in boiler.
Heat until jello dissolves; cool.
Then mix in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: excellent strawberry pie(very easy)
directions: Fold together the first three ingredients.
Add strawberries. Place in graham cracker crusts.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Mix taco mix with beef. While this is simmering, mash potatoes and add corn and beans (drained).
Pour into deep pan.
Then put meat on top.
Fix cornbread mix according to directions on package.
Pour on top and cook at 350° until cornbread is done (about 45 minutes).

title: classic chicken divan(a dish that is a meal in itself)
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add chicken broth, stirring until thick.
Stir in cream, sherry, salt and pepper.
Place broccoli crosswise in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 the sauce over broccoli; top with chicken slices.
Add Parmesan cheese to remaining sauce; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Broil until sauce is golden.
Can be frozen in freezer to oven type baking dish. It can also be made and stored in refrigerator the day before it is to be baked.
Serves 8.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Beat eggs until fluffy. Add eggs to bread cubes and stir.
Add onions, celery and melted margarine to bread and stir.
Add parsley flakes.
Stuffing can be put into turkey or chicken or baked in casserole dish.
It can also be frozen.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix all together and pour in 10 x 10-inch cake pan.
Cook at 350°.

title: cereal peanut bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, combine corn syrup, brown sugar and dash of salt.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies, cornflakes and chocolate chips.
Press into prepared pan.
Cover and chill 1 hour. Cut into bars.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Press dough in 9 x 13-inch pan; pat out.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar, blending well.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, starting with the cream cheese and ending with the lemon juice and shrimp.
Serve on a variety of crackers.

title: chicken breasts en casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts with 1 tablespoon butter until fully cooked.
In a shallow baking dish, layer first the chicken, then the ham and cheese for 6 individual servings.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add milk carefully; season.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Beat egg and cream together and add to sauce, cooking a few minutes more. Spread the sauce over the meat in the casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and parsley flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted butter (reserve 1 tablespoon butter) until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; press firmly to seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 meat mixture into each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture.
Twist slightly to seal edges.
Brush top with reserved margarine and dip into crushed crouton crumbs. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
These make great appetizers.

title: vodka slush
directions: Heat water and sugar to dissolve.
Mix fruit juices with the water and sugar.
Add vodka and vermouth; freeze.
Fill glass 1/2 full of slush.
Add white soda or 50-50.

title: two jiffy pies(no cooking)
directions: Combine pineapple pieces, milk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Put lemon in last.
Mix well.
Fold into graham crusts.

title: rosy holiday punch
directions: In punch bowl, dissolve flavor crystals in grape juice.
Just before serving, add club soda or water.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: divinity
directions: Mix and cook to soft ball stage.
While cooking, beat 2 eggs until peaks form.
Slowly pour 1/2 syrup into egg mixture while beating.
Continue beating while returning remaining syrup to cook until it spins a thin thread.
Slowly add to beating mixture.
Beat for about 10 minutes.
Add vanilla (1 teaspoon) and nuts to taste. Spoon quickly on waxed paper.

title: edna's sugar cookies
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Beat together the next 4 ingredients.
Mix both together.
Add the flour.
Chill.
Roll in balls; mash with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 11 minutes.

title: cake brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand until smooth.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° until done (30 minutes).
Easy and simple.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until tender; drain. Combine carrots, onion and pepper; set aside.
Combine soup, vinegar, oil, sugar and mustard; stir until well mixed.
Pour over vegetables; toss lightly.
Refrigerate at least overnight.

title: beef stew
directions: Put vegetables and meat in baking dish and mix.
Pour tomato sauce, sugar, water, Worcestershire sauce and tapioca over meat. Bake at 250° for 5 hours, covered.

title: salmon with mustard sauce
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients to make sauce.
Put salmon steaks on foil and broil 6 inches from burner for 7 minutes.
Remove and turn.
Spread each generously with cream sauce.
Return to broiler and broil 5 minutes or longer (until it flakes when separated with a fork).
Serve with any leftover sauce.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt oleo in scalded milk.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix together and let rise for 15 minutes. Make dough into rolls and let rise for 15 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southern indian style green bean curry
directions: Heat oil.
When hot, add mustard seed.
When seed makes crackling sound, lower heat and add salt, spices and the frozen green beans.
Saute on medium heat until beans are cooked.
May add a tablespoon of water, if needed, to help cook.
When done, remove from heat and mix with fresh coconut.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies with icing center until mixture resembles dirt. Set aside.
Cream the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. Mix pudding mixes and milk until well blended.
Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture with rubber spatula.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: sliced apples with cheese casserole
directions: Soften cheese and margarine.
Stir in flour and sugar.
Put apples in casserole dish.
Add cheese topping mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Place in cold oven at 325° and bake for 2 hours or less.
Be sure to fill pan only 3/4 full and grease and flour pan; tube pan is best.

title: nancy sherman's mother-in-law bean salad(sweet and sour)
directions: Use large container.
Drain all beans, putting kidney and garbanzo beans in first, letting the liquid from other cans gently rinse the first beans.
Place beans in large container.
Nancy uses a plastic bread storage container that she only uses for bean salad, as it picks up the onion flavor.
Add the salt, pepper, green pepper, celery and red onion.
Put sugar, vinegar and oil in a blender.
Blend on high for at least 2 minutes, or until mixture no longer separates when you turn off machine.
Pour oil and vinegar mixture over beans and vegetables; stir gently. Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon in hot oil.
Make sure oil is deep.

title: quiche bars
directions: Combine crackers and flour; cut in butter until mixture forms a ball.
Press evenly against bottom of 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan; prick bottom.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
In 2 tablespoons bacon fat, saute onion until golden, set aside.
Beat together next 5 ingredients.
Spread grated cheese evenly over crust.
Mix together onion, crumbled bacon, pimentos and parsley.
Sprinkle on top of grated cheese.
Carefully pour egg mixture over onions and cheese.
Bake in a preheated hot oven at 400° about 25 to 30 minutes or until golden and just set.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
May be served warm or cold.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes about 75 bars.

title: granny's oatmeal cake
directions: Combine boiling water, butter or oleo and oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: apricot fruit salad
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 1 cup juice.
Drain pineapple.
Mix reserved apricot juice with pudding and cook until thick.
Cool. Add fruits and pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: tomato jam
directions: Boil tomatoes, chopped, with sugar for 10 minutes.
Add lemon and jello.
Boil another 10 minutes, then pour into jars and seal. Store in refrigerator.

title: south of the border squash casserole
directions: Saute squash and onion in butter.
Add chiles, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Spray inside of crock-pot with cooking spray. Add hamburger, beans, tomatoes, onion and chili mix. Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cheese, mayonnaise or salad dressing, onion and catsup in small bowl on medium speed until well blended.
Add shrimp and beat on slow speed for for 30 seconds.
Chill several hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with Bugles corn snacks.
Makes 2 cups.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine bread crumbs, eggs and milk; stir in sugar, lemon juice and seasonings.
Add ground meat and mix thoroughly.
Press mixture into a loaf.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies(7 dozen)
directions: Combine butter, sugars (both), pudding mix and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs; add flour and baking soda.
Then stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pork chop onion rice bake
directions: Brown chops in lard or Crisco.
Spread rice in bottom of rectangular baking dish (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch).
Reserve 1 tablespoon of seasonings from envelope of onion soup mix and sprinkle remaining seasonings and bits of onion over rice.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid and distribute mushrooms and pimento over rice.
Add hot water to reserved mushroom liquid to total 3 cups liquid and pour over rice.
Arrange browned chops on top of rice mixture and sprinkle chops with reserved seasonings.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Do
not
skin
tomatoes;
cut
in quarters and place in heavy pot
with
celery,
green pepper and bay leaves.
Cover tightly and
cook
on low to medium heat without adding water. Put through sieve,
add
all
the rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Serves about 6.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, butter and 4 tablespoons of sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/2 cup for topping whipped cream.
Add remaining sugar.
Fold in marshmallows and spread on crust base.
Over this, spread cherry pie mix, then remainder of crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cocktail chicken wings
directions: Line baking pan with aluminum foil so it is easier to clean. Place chicken wing pieces in a single layer in pan.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over wings.
Cover with foil, shiny side to chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and allow to brown for a half hour longer.

title: chicken and cream
directions: Place chicken in oven dish, mix other ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: evelyn's gingerbread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Servings:
Add some whipped cream on top and enjoy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on 300° wrapped in aluminum foil.
Uncover and brown.
Cook about 1 hour.

title: dump cake 1
directions: Put filling in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pineapple over filling. Spread dry cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted butter over dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: b and a home fries
directions: First get a big frying pan and put 2 tablespoons of butter in it.
Fry on medium to high until melted.
Then slice potatoes thin and put into frypan.
Proceed to slicing the mushrooms, peppers and onion.
Put these in pan also.
Add salt and pepper and Creole seasoning.
Cover for 10 minutes.
Then add last 2 tablespoons of butter.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Cream in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour.
Stir in milk and lemon extract.
Pour into Bundt pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Mix together powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Glaze cake.

title: snowball cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; let set until jelled.
Whip the Dream Whip as directed on the package and fold into the jelled mixture.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble 1/2 of an angel food cake. Cover with half of the gelatine mixture.
Repeat.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Serves 15.
Rich, but delicious!

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese and add Ro-Tel tomatoes and browned hamburger. Great!!!

title: corn relish
directions: Blanch corn 2 minutes.
Drop into cold water before cutting from cob.
Chop peppers and cabbage.
Cook all together for 20 minutes.
After you pack in jars, simmer for 25 minutes.

title: granpolly's bread
directions: Dissolve and set aside the water and yeast.
Mix with dough hook the wheat flour, sugar, milk and salt.
Add applesauce and yeast water from above.
Mix in 2 cups flour.
Cover with plastic wrap; place in warm oven 15 to 30 minutes.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes. Form into loaves.
Place in lightly greased pans, covered with plastic wrap.
Let rise in warm oven 15 to 20 minutes, not above the top of the pan.
Turn on oven to 325°; bake 25 to 30 minutes for small pans.

title: crusty buttermilk cornbread
directions: Combine flour(s), cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center of the dry mixture and add the egg.
Stir in the buttermilk and mix.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking tin with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, eggs, flour, soda, allspice, cinnamon and diced apples.
Batter will be stiff.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all but the parsley and pecans (use beaters or hand--DO NOT use food processor).
Chill for several hours.
Roll into ball shape.
MIx parsley with the pecans and roll the salmon ball mixture in them until coated.
Return to refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: snack bars
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Combine eggs and butter and add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chips.
Transfer to a greased 9 X 13 baking pan and bake at 350 degrees for 25 -30 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle with candy bar pieces and cool.
Cut into bars.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger
with
salad
oil and cloves of garlic. Add tomato
sauce,
tomatoes, salt, oregano and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mix together squash, onion, oleo, salt and pepper.
Mix together eggs and milk in a baking dish. Put half of squash mixture, 1/2 cracker crumbs and 1/2 cheese. Pour 1/2 of milk and egg mixture over squash.
Repeat layers. Cook for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, crumbs, onion, milk, egg and next 4 season ings.
Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in a large skillet; brown meatballs.
Remove meatballs from skillet; drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly in skillet until jelly is melted, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs and stir until coated. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot in a chafing dish.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar and eggs, then 1/4 cup hot water.
Mix can milk and flour together, then add to egg mixture, then add vanilla.
Pour into ice cream freezer and add whole milk.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine the flour and cornmeal; stir in the chopped onion. Beat together the egg and buttermilk; add to dry ingredients.
Mix together and drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan with wax paper.
Have 60 (1-inch) fluted foil candy cups ready.
Beat peanut butter, margarine and vanilla in a medium size bowl until blended.
Stir in sugar until well blended.
Roll a level 1/2 teaspoon mix into balls.
Place on prepared pan and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix brown sugar,
flour, salt and pumpkin pie spice (or 1 teaspoon cinnamon,
1/2 teaspoon nutmeg, 1/4 teaspoon ginger and 1/4 teaspoon
cloves).
Add
canned pumpkin, Pet milk, egg and molasses; beat
until
smooth.
Pour
into deep 9-inch pie pan lined with
unbaked pastry.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to slow
and
bake
until
firm
or about 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and mix in all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Gently fold cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and dry gelatin into prepared whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Spoon into individual serving dishes and garnish each serving with strawberry slices and mint, if desired.

title: frozen fruit yogurt
directions: In food processor, pulse three times with metal blade, then run continuously to chop the frozen berries finely.
Add yogurt, lemon juice and sugar.
Run until smooth and creamy.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 1 pint.

title: chocolate covered pecan fritters
directions: Combine caramels and milk in top of double boiler.
Heat until caramels melt, stirring occasionally.
Beat with a wooden spoon until creamy.
Add pecans; stir well to combine.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered wax paper.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Combine chocolate bar and paraffin in top of double boiler; heat until melted and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Dip each fritter into chocolate with a toothpick.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Cook about 1 quart cut up zucchini or yellow squash until tender.
Drain and chop coarsely.
In a small skillet, cook a large chopped onion in butter until soft.
Add 1/2 cup cream and 5 or 6 saltines or some bread crumbs.
Combine squash and onion mixture; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased casserole; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are brown.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add raisins and milk.
Mix and place in greased baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, boiling water and butter.
Pour over batter and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil. Add nuts. When mixture darkens a bit, add butter.
When mixture starts to boil and become brown, remove from heat.
Add salt and baking soda, mixing well. Pour immediately into buttered pans and pound to get air bubbles out.
When cool, remove from pans.

title: maxwell's spinach salad
directions: Arrange spinach in a large bowl.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve accompanied by Maxwell's Spinach Salad Dressing.
Serves 1 large salad.

title: working for peanut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except pie crust) in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Put in pie crust. Let set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add beaten eggs.
Cook until thick.
Beat in salad dressing. Toss together with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: rabbit in brown sauce
directions: Wash and drain meat. In a large black iron pot, heat oil.
Add rabbit, frying until dark brown. Add vegetables, browning while stirring. Add all other ingredients, stirring.
Place cornstarch in a cup.
Add cold water slowly, stirring to a thick paste.
Stir paste into pot.
Add water for correct consistency.
Serve rabbit and sauce over hot rice.

title: peach pickles
directions: Pare hard ripe fruit.
Leave whole.
Boil sugar, spices, water and vinegar.
Add peaches and cook until tender.
Pack peaches into hot jars.
Pour boiling syrup over peaches.
Process 10 minutes in hot water bath or put into freezer containers and freeze.

title: tailgating chicken chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water. Drain. Pour into pan and cover with 2-inches of cold water. Simmer beans until tender and drain. Saute onions in 4 tablespoons of butter until soft. Melt remaining butter in separate heavy pan. Stir in cooked onion, then add broth and half and half, whisking constantly. Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in Tabasco, chili powder, cumin, salt and white pepper. Add beans, chilies, chicken and cheese. Simmer, stirring, for 20 minutes. Stir sour cream into chili before serving.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Chop up fruit; mix up chocolate or vanilla pudding according to directions on box. Put sprinkles on top of pudding. Dip fruit and enjoy.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and butter.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Stir in sugar, eggs, flour, salt and soda, then stir in spices. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon jello pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken. Cool, debone and chop. Saute onion and celery. Mix chicken, onion and celery with soups, sour cream and almonds. Put in casserole.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Grind the beef, salt pork, and bread together twice using a meat grinder or food processor. Combine with the egg, sugar, allspice, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Shape into 1 inch balls.
Melt the shortening in a skillet and brown the meatballs.
Transfer to a shallow casserole, pour on the beef broth, cover with foil, and bake for 45 minutes.
Add the cream and cook without a cover for 15 minutes more.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, chili powder, garlic and onion salt, catsup and tomatoes.
Add milk.
Add Velveeta.
Cook until thickened.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add melted oleo, vanilla and milk.
Pour into raw pie crust.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bride's pink punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in water.
Add sugar and stir in gelatin mixture.
Add pineapple juice.
Refrigerate.
Add beverage before serving.
Add sherbet last.
May use vanilla ice cream.
Serves 35.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together and make ball.
Roll in 1 cup crushed pecans on wax paper to store.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Beat 3 egg whites stiff.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, crushed crackers fine, chopped nuts and baking powder.
Mix into egg whites.
Melt butter into 8-inch pie pan.
Then pour mixture into pan to make crust.	Double recipe for 9 x 13 pan.
Cook 30 minutes at 325°. Top crust with peaches.
Finish with Cool Whip over peaches.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mince the salmon with a fork.
Add eggs and other ingredients. Make into a loaf and put into a greased loaf pan to bake.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
The rest of the celery soup can be diluted and used as a sauce.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Combine the white chocolate and water, stirring until chocolate melts.
Set aside.
Cream the butter; gradually add the sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in the white chocolate mixture and the vanilla.
Combine the cake flour and soda; add to chocolate mixture, alternately with the buttermilk, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Beat the egg whites (which should be at room temperature).

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage, drain and set aside.
Blend flour and black pepper into drippings and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Gradually add milk; cook until thickened.
Add cut-up sausage.
Serve warm.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Alternate slices of sweet potatoes and orange slices in layers, ending with potatoes.
Combine remaining 4 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix butter, eggs and sugar well.
Add flour, vanilla, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add apples.
Batter will be very stiff and will absorb moisture from apples.
Bake in an ungreased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef tips in sauce
directions: Coat meat in 2 tablespoons of flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Shake in bag.
Brown.
Add onion and garlic and cook for 3 minutes.
Add gravy, mushrooms, basil and water.
Cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes, or until meat is tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour
into a well-greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: marge's good cookies
directions: Beat together the oil and oleo, then add the sugars.
Beat and add the egg and then the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and make into small balls and flatten with a fork.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar and karo.
Cook until peanuts crackle and syrup darkens.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and stir. Pour into buttered pan.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco until it is like corn meal.
Add water, salt and baking powder.
Mix until it all becomes a ball.
Roll into crusts.
It makes 3 large pie crusts, plus one 9-inch!

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips and nuts, on low speed until mixed.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in chips and nuts. Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before turning it out.

title: pork chops supreme casserole
directions: Pare and slice 4 medium potatoes.
Place in medium size casserole dish.
Lightly
season
with
salt
and
pepper.	In mixing bowl,
mix
soup and milk.
Fry pork chops until golden brown.
Drain
chops on paper towel and arrange over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: We like over plain Bugles or with crisp veggies.

title: nilla wafer banana rama
directions: Make jello as directed on box.
Line a bowl with a small amount of pudding.
Add a layer of banana slices and top with a layer of Nilla Wafers.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding on top. Cover with Cool Whip and chill before serving.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 3 hours at 300°.
During the first hour, stir 3 times with a fork so rice won't settle.
After first hour, stir in 1/2 cup raisins, dates or figs.

title: glazed chicken breast and rice
directions: Combine 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and flour. Dredge chicken with flour mixture; brown on both sides in oil in a Dutch oven.
Add beef consomme; cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carne guisada
directions: Cook steak in oil in large heavy skillet over medium-high heat, stirring continually, until browned.
Sprinkle flour over beef and stir thoroughly.
Add onion and remaining ingredients. Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 40 minutes or until meat is tender and sauce is thickened.
Serve mixture in flour tortillas.
Yields 4 cups.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites, 1 cup sugar and baking powder well.
Add Ritz crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased metal pie plate approximately 50 minutes at 300°.
Whip cream, vanilla and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Cover top and chill until served.

title: backwoods campfire potatoes
directions: Layer all on double sheets of heavy-duty foil.
Cook on campfire 30 minutes.
Turn and cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crispy butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg whites and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Chill.
Roll into 1/2 inch balls, then roll in sugar.
Place on baking sheet, flatten with fork or fancy glass bottom.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: no bake low-calorie cheese cake
directions: Mix sugar with cream cheese.
Add the sour cream, whipped topping and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and pour into the pie shell. Refrigerate for several hours.
Serves 10.

title: pecan coconut bonbons
directions: Combine sugar, coconut, milk and nuts.
Stir with wooden spoon until blended well.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Put additional coconut in bowl.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll ball into coconut.
Place on cookie sheets and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: dried beef roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine dried beef, cream cheese, horseradish and dry mustard (using half of finely ground dried beef, saving other half for rolling).
Mix well.
Shape into 50 (3/4-inch) balls.
Roll each ball in dried beef.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
To serve insert one pretzel stick into each ball.
Balls can be made ahead and frozen until needed.
Allow to thaw completely before inserting pretzel stick.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining dough ingredients; beat vigorously about 20 strokes.
Allow dough to rest 5 minutes; then roll out your dough for your pizza.

title: onion soup au gratin
directions: Melt butter in a large soup pot.
Add onions and wilt over medium-low heat, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Sprinkle sugar over onions; toss.
Cook, uncovered, until caramelized, 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper.
Add 3 cups of stock; simmer, uncovered, over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add remaining 3 cups of stock and wine.
Cook until rich in taste, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix melted butter and cookie crumbs together (use enough butter so crumbs hold together).
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine ice cream, creme de menthe and food coloring.
Pour over crust and refrigerate.

title: bean and broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in a little margarine until limp in a large pan. Add broccoli with a little water.
Cook until broccoli is done. Add bouillon cube to soup.
Add beans and approximately
3 to 4 cups.
Cook until things are good and hot.
Thicken with flour and continue cooking until desired consistency.

title: bean soup(6 quarts)
directions: Soak the beans in water for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Wash them into a 6-quart stockpot; just cover with water.
Add salt to taste (may take 2 to 3 teaspoons).
Cover with lid; cook until tender.
Add more water during cooking, if necessary.
Add enough milk to make it soupy.
Add the onions.
A cup of diced celery or cooked spinach enhances it, too.
Add a cup of tomato soup, plain tomato juice or even catsup, but use less of this.
Sprinkle in some Accent and garlic powder seasoning (a teaspoon or more of each according to your preference).
Let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. If the milk doesn't get a little thickish, rub some softened butter in with 2 tablespoons flour to make a paste.
Add a bit of bean liquid and stir, then pour back into the pot.

title: tater-topped casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook onion, celery and ground beef until the meat is brown and the vegetables are tender; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread soup over meat mixture.
Top with frozen potatoes.

title: emeril's pancakes
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Add buttermilk, the egg and 1 tablespoon oil. (Lumps are ok.) Let batter stand, covered, in refrigerator for at least 1 hour. If necessary, thin with extra buttermilk after resting.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, egg and applesauce.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add water, raisins and pecans.
Pour in well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use half of 1 (8 ounce) carton of Cool Whip as icing.

title: makes its own crust cherry cobbler
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, egg, milk, flour and butter.
Beat well. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart deep baking dish.
Combine remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar and cherries in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over batter.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is brown and crusty.
Yields 6 servings.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix.
Add salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add milk, then flour.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Bake filling in crust.
Is enough for 2 pies.
Keep some to put on top.

title: hot dried beef spread
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, milk and Worcestershire sauce and beat until fluffy.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: no crust sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm or cool with a spoon of whipped cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients on stove until butter melts.
Brush liberally over chicken when grilling.
Delicious!!

title: lentil(soup)
directions: Place all ingredients in a suitable size pot with enough water to make a soup thickness to one's liking.
Cook at medium heat (about 1 1/2 hours or until done).

title: fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and dust with flour two 9-inch or 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Sift the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
Cream shortening. Add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with sour milk.
Mix cocoa and hot water to form a smooth paste; beat into batter.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, and peppers, bring to boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cool a little bit and add Certo and food coloring.
Put in jars and seal with wax.
Serve on crackers with cream cheese. (I like to strain the jelly.
Some people like white vinegar.)

title: red velvet cake and frosting
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Flour and grease pan (2 round or 1 sheet cake pan).

title: pan fried liver and onions
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, fry bacon until crisp over medium heat; drain well and keep warm.
Pour off all the fat except 2 tablespoons from the skillet.
Trim amy membrane from the edges of the liver.
Salt and pepper and coat with flour.
Fry over medium heat in hot fat for about 4 minutes, turning once.
Fry crisp and brown on the outside.
Place liver and bacon on warm platter and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Remove the center of the bread, leaving 1-inch on the bottom (this becomes your bowl).
Reserve the portion you removed and tear it in small bite sized pieces.
Mix ingredients well.
Spoon into cavity.
Arrange pieces of bread around the bread bowl.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Press evenly onto bottom of a spring-form pan.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Squeeze spinach dry.
Melt butter in a 9 by 13 or jellyroll pan.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl beat eggs, flour, milk, and seasonings.
Add cheese, spinach, and onion.
Pour into baking dish and bake 25-35 minutes. Cool for 45 minutes to set.
Cut into bite sized squares.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs very well.
Add sugar, beat well again.
Add vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Mix well, then add boiling milk and blend in with spoon or whip.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This cake is great for shortcake.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and water.
Cook until drop in water forms hard ball.
Pour hot mixture very slowly into eggs, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans and beat until mixture thickens.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: pork-wine dish
directions: Cut orange peel in small pieces; wash thoroughly, running through cold water several times.
Also let soak in heavily salted water several hours, rinsing several times thereafter.
Very important to rinse many times; otherwise peel will give a bitter taste to hot dish.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut top out of the bell peppers and take seeds out; set aside.
Boil for 5 minutes in salty water.
Cook ground beef, onions and pepper until ground beef is brown and onions tender. Add chopped tomatoes; simmer for about 4 minutes or until tomatoes are cooked.
Drain off liquid.
Stir in rice, salt, basil and pepper.
Stuff peppers with the meat mixture.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Toss together bread crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle on top of peppers.
Cook in 350° oven.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cover bread with milk for five minutes. Add sugar, eggs, melted butter, salt, vanilla and cinnamon. Mix well. Pour into a buttered bread pan. Set pan in pan of warm water and bake 1 hour at 325. Serves 6 to 8.

title: curry pickles
directions: Soak pickles in salt water for 3 hours.
Boil together vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and curry powder.
Add drained pickles.
Heat to boiling.
Can in quarts jars and seal.

title: cindy's little smokies
directions: Heat and mix chili sauce and jelly.
Cook until thick.
Add sausages and cook until heated through.
(These are better if allowed to cook a while.)
Makes 50.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: In saucepan over low heat, combine chicken, cream cheese, peppers and 1/2 cup picante sauce. Roll combination into tortillas and place in 8 x 12-inch pan, seam side down. In saucepan, combine Velveeta and milk over low heat. Pour over enchiladas and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cover pan with aluminum foil. Pour remaining picante sauce over and serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add beans, one can at a time.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: eclair cake dessert
directions: Layer graham crackers on bottom of greased pan.
Add milk to pudding; fold in Cool Whip.
Add half of filling on top of graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers; top with remaining filling.
Top with one can of chocolate frosting.

title: mexican fiesta biscuit bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in oven in a 13 x 9-inch glass or non-aluminum baking pan.
Separate biscuit dough.
Cut each biscuit into eighths.
Place biscuit pieces in large bowl. Toss with salsa.
Spoon evenly into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, bell pepper, onions and olives.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve with remaining 1 cup salsa.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Boil and let cool.
Mix rest of ingredients and combine with first mixture.
Refrigerate and let set overnight.
Will keep 1 to 2 weeks.

title: yum yumm cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Grease and flour 11 x 17-inch pan. Bake cake and cool.
Soften cream cheese and beat together with milk and pudding.
Spread over cooled cake.
Drain pineapple well and spread over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple layer, then sprinkle with coconut and nuts, as desired.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add sugar to taste.
Freeze half of the recipe for ice when used.
Yields 35 to 40 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Pour some sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Add a layer of macaroni (about 1/2), green peppers, pepperoni, mushrooms, cheese and more sauce.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: good time party punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Then add last 2 and stir.
Serve immediately.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first 8 ingredients, then stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.

title: ice cream muffins
directions: Use any flavor ice cream desired.
Butter almond, butter pecan and almond toffee are especially good. Mix ingredients (batter will be stiff).
Put in greased muffin tins and bake at 475° until done, about 15 minutes.

title: deborah's fast chops
directions: Put chops in deep
saucepan;
do not overlap the chops. Pour your choice of soup
over
the chops with 1 can of water. Bake at 350°.
Cooks in about 15 minutes.

title: rich banana dessert
directions: Mix the flour, butter and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Boil together and cool.
Pour over pickles and freeze.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine in saucepan; boil slowly 10 to 15 minutes.
Take the skin off chicken and cook until done.
Take out of water; put in baking pan.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: breaded chicken cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. To bread crumbs, add thyme, lemon zest, salt and pepper. Pound each breast to equal thickness. Put flour, eggs and bread crumbs each separately in 3 shallow dishes. Pat chicken dry and season both sides with salt and pepper. Dip each breast into flour, then egg and bread crumbs. Lay on a piece of wax paper. Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Add oil. Lay 2 breasts smooth side down. Cook chicken about 2 minutes; turn and cook additional 2 minutes. Drain and place on baking pan. Bake until firm to touch, about 8 minutes.

title: me-maw blackwell's pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Makes 1 pie.
Mix the ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Use butter to saute onion until tender and glistening. Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Garnish with cheese and croutons.

title: file gumbo
directions: Make brown gravy with oil, flour and water in a large pot. Add other ingredients except chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in ovenproof serving dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or pastry shell.

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: With fingers, shred beef into small pieces.
Cover with boiling water to freshen.
Drain well and set aside.
In a heavy 1 1/2-quart pan, melt butter and add flour. Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and slowly add milk, stirring constantly, to blend.
Add the pepper, optional nutmeg and drained beef.
Return to heat.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture has thickened. Serve over biscuits, toast or waffles.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Layer Tater Tots in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and onions until lightly brown.
Drain off fat and sprinkle over Tater Tots.
Mix soups together and pour over mixture (can add 1/2 can water).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese last few minutes of baking time.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut chops to form a pocket. Chop raisins and combine with rest of ingredients. Stuff chops with dressing. Fasten opening with toothpicks. Flour chops; brown in hot fat and season with salt and pepper. Add a few tablespoons water; cover skillet. Cook at low temperature for 35 to 40 minutes until tender.

title: no-peek dumplings
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in pan and boil until chicken is done.
Cool and debone chicken.
Combine next 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir until moistened.
Drop by tablespoon into boiling broth.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat and don't peek. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together well; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the chicken in a cup or bowl to make the sauce.
After you wash and dry the chicken.
Coat the pieces or brush the whole bird with the mixture.
Reserve some sauce.
Bake the chicken in a pan coated with nonstick spray. Baste periodically with reserved sauce.
If the chicken gets too brown too quickly, cover with aluminum foil until done.

title: tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in saucepan.
Add sugar, cinnamon and lemon jello (dry).
Boil a few minutes.
Cool and use as a vegetable or put into freezer containers for further use.

title: fresh cranberry sauerbraten
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat on all sides in oil.
Add onions, cranberries, sugar, vinegar, 1 1/2 cups water, cloves and garlic powder.
Simmer, covered, 2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until tender. Remove meat to platter; keep warm.
Mix cornstarch to smooth paste with 2 tablespoons water; stir into cranberry mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until gravy thickens and clears.
Serve with hot pot roast and mashed potatoes.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap chicken with bacon; fasten with toothpicks.
Cover bottom of a casserole pan with dried beef.
Arrange chicken on top.
Mix soup, sour cream and cream cheese; spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, white sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg well.
Place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/3 cup flour, 1 cup uncooked oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/3 c. melted oleo.
Spread over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: baked hamburger dish
directions: Fry hamburger, celery and onions together until done. Add remaining ingredients. Put into baking dish. Sprinkle top with chow mein noodles or potato chips, crushed. Bake an hour or more at 325°.

title: peach angel dessert(low calorie)
directions: In a small saucepan combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually whisk in water, and corn syrup until smooth.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to boil.
Cook 1-2 minutes or until thickens. Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature, stirring several times.
Cut angel food cake into nine slices.
Line an ungreased 13x9x2 dish with the slices.
In a mixing bowl beat cream cheese and milk until blended.
Gradually beat in confectioner sugar.
Set aside 1/3 cup whipped topping for garnish.
Fold remaining whipped topping into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over cake.
Top with peaches.
Pour gelatin mixture over peaches.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or longer. Cut into squares and top each piece with Whipped Topping.

title: parmesan crisps
directions: Lightly spray one side of each tortilla with olive-oil flavored cooking spray.
Combine garlic powder, cheese and chili powder in a small bowl.
Sprinkle evenly over tortillas.
With scissors, cut each tortilla into 8 wedges and arrange on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until crisp and slightly browned, about 7 minutes.
Makes 24 wedges.

title: cold cut pizza
directions: Line bottom of two 10-inch pie plates with crust.
Blend all ingredients; add to pie pans.
Add top crust.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Prick the top; spread egg yolks on top crust (egg wash).
Bake again, until crust is golden (20 to 30 minutes).

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Add garlic to melted butter and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix together bread crumbs and cheese.
Salt and pepper the chicken and dip in melted butter, then into crumb mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: himmel und erde (heaven and earth)
directions: Fry bacon; drain fat.
Add onions.
Fry until onions sweat. Put potatoes in casserole raw.
Add apples and bacon-onion mixture.
Add 1 handful of sugar, a glug of apple cider vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sharon's brownies
directions: Melt margarine, oil, water and Nestle Quik.
Add flour and sugar.
Add butter, vanilla, eggs and soda.
Place in greased 11 x 15-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 1/2 to 3-quart to 2 1/2 to 3-inch deep baking dish.
In food processor finely chop sweet potatoes into chunks.
In large mixing bowl, add potatoes.
Mix in remaining ingredients except 1 cup of cream.
Put into food processor and mix until blended.
Pour over potatoes, add remaining cup of cream and stir until well blended.
Pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes, then stir mixture near edge to middle.
Bake 15 minutes. Then stir again.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top is slightly brown and custard is firm.

title: chicken-artichoke casserole
directions: Weigh chicken after it is skinned and boned.
Salt, pepper and paprika chicken pieces.
Brown chicken in 4 tablespoons of butter. Place in a large casserole (I use a large, flat Pyrex pan).
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons of butter in same frying pan and saute mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over them and stir in chicken
broth and sherry.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Arrange artichoke hearts, without cutting them in pieces, between chicken pieces. Pour mushroom-sherry sauce over them; cover and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, soup and soy sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add chicken and rice.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Put noodles and cashews on top and bake 2 more minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Add milk, vanilla and butter. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter until it melts. Add oatmeal and nuts; mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: icebox cherry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with juice from 2 lemons, then add other ingredients, adding whipping cream last.

title: mom's goulash
directions: Brown onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add ground beef.
Let cook a few minutes.
Add other ingredients.

title: creative (play) dough
directions: Cook all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes, stirring vigorously, until mixture forms a ball. Remove dough from saucepan and let stand on counter 5 minutes.

title: greek stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine butter, onion, parsley and juice drained from tomatoes.
Cook down to about half.
Add tomatoes, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Salt to taste.
Heat through.
Serve in sauce dishes topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix onions, green peppers, carrots and ground meat together. Add cracker crumbs, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Add tomato juice and blend well.
Shape into a loaf and place in oiled casserole.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes. Uncover and bake for another 20 minutes.

title: fried crab patties
directions: Mix crab, crumbs, pepper, onions and celery.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, A.1. Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into patties.
Fry in deep fat.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream
shortening,
sugar, peanut butter and eggs well. Add flour
and	vanilla
and
roll into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with fork crosswise.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hijiki barazushi
directions: Cook rice and mix in vinegar, sugar and salt mix.
Saute the other ingredients with oil.
Add water, sugar and shoyu; cook until done.
Mix with flavored rice.
For rice, vinegar and sugar, use the plastic measuring cup from the rice cooker.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Heat oil in iron skillet in oven while mixing remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into skillet; spread.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese sauce for vegetables
directions: Melt cheese; set aside.
Mix flour into melted butter. Gradually add juice until well blended.
Add melted cheese and chopped boiled eggs into sauce.
Pour over vegetables.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
In large skillet heat shortening and brown meat, turning frequently.
Stir in onion soup mix and 2 cups water after meat is brown.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in green peppers and simmer 10 minutes or until meat is tender. Blend cornstarch or flour with 1/2 cup water.
Stir just enough into skillet to thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: cucumber summer salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Chill in refrigerator overnight, letting all the flavorings penetrate the cucumber while tightly covered.
Preferably in a Tupperware bowl. Serve as a side dish with chicken or beef entrees.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Combine Bisquick and cinnamon.
Add milk, egg and pumpkin until blended.
Drop by 1/4 to 1/2 cup on hot greased griddle. Spread out with back of spoon.
When bubbles appear on top, turn and brown other side.
Serve with butter or syrup.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: republican cake
directions: Mix and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook and drain bacon; crumble.
Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
In small bowl, combine catsup, vinegar, brown sugar and mustard.
Mix all these with the baked beans, the kidney beans (drained) and the lima beans (drain 1/2 of the juice).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease baking dish; scald milk and beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir and add a sprinkle of salt.
Add bread and stir.
Add raisins and mix just enough so raisins don't sink and dot with butter.
Set baking dish in about 2 inches of warm water while baking.
Bake at 350° for about an hour, or until knife comes out clean.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Bring peaches and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and stir for 2 minutes to dissolve.
When cool, fold in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour into an oblong casserole dish and refrigerate.
Microwave almonds on High for 5 minutes or until golden.
When cool, sprinkle on top of salad.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: golden punch(serves 16)
directions: Combine orange juice, lemon juice, pineapple juice and cherry juice; mix well.
Pour over ice, add cold ginger ale.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat altogether.
Cook in double boiler until it thickens. Chill.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add milk and half and half.
Stir all together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Add cinnamon on top.
Bake until done in 350° oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sauted vegetables
directions: Mix zucchini and tomatoes and season with basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Saute in a little oil or oleo.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth. Spread over cake when cool. You might have to thin it with cream if it is too thick.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork in mushroom sauce
directions: Flour meat and brown in oil.
Place meat in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Place onions on top of meat and season to taste.
Mix soup and water together and pour over meat.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add the mushrooms the last 15 minutes of cooking time.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave caramel nut sticky buns
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, water and cinnamon in 4-cup microwaveproof ring mold.
Place in oven.
Cook on High 1 minute. Remove and stir in nuts.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Place in brown sugar mixture.
Stir carefully to coat each piece.
Push biscuits toward outside of mold.
Place in oven.
Cook on High 3 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Pull biscuits apart to serve.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour first 5 ingredients into a buttered deep dish.
Combine next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add in egg; mix until crumbly. Spread over cherry mix.
Pour melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets with vegetables
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Dip in beaten eggs, then shake in equal mixture of bread crumbs (flavored or plain) and Parmesan cheese (I use a plastic bag to shake the meat in).
Saute in generous amount of butter until golden brown.
Remove chicken to a casserole dish (or baking pan).
Saute vegetables in the same pan, scraping the bits of chicken up while frying vegetables.
Add vegetables to the chicken; mix all together.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup of broth to pan and heat; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and somewhat crispy on top, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with any kind of rice.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir at least half of the hot mixture gradually into egg yolks.
Blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses and mix well.
Blend soda with milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Bake in a moderate oven (340°) for about 40 minutes.
Cut into squares while slightly warm.

title: fettuccine with lobster and yellow squash
directions: Heat large pot of water to boiling for pasta.
