Combine oil, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper and chives in a large bowl.
Whisk until combined.
Set aside.
In another large pot, place squash and lobster in steamer basket over simmering water.
Steam 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Add to chive dressing.

title: ruby's hot dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use green peppers to taste, depending on how hot you desire the dip to be.
Blend peppers in blender with vinegar.
Drain well.

title: oven-baked brisket
directions: Saturate brisket with seasonings and sauces.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: orange salad(can be used as salad or dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except sour cream.
Chill in refrigerator.
Take out of refrigerator after chilled and fold in sour cream.

title: easy pasta sauce
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in medium saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling, Reduce heat; boil gently, uncovered, 30 min. Remove Bay Leaf.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.

title: cheese ball on a stick
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, onion and ripe olives.
Shape in 36 balls.
Roll in dried beef.
Chill. Insert 1 pretzel stick in each ball just before serving.
Yields 36 appetizers.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Select small, firm, yellow or red tomatoes.
Wash and drain. If a tomato preserve with skins is desired, dip the tomatoes into boiling water, then into cold water and remove skins.
Handle carefully.
Boil lemon 5 minutes in part of water.
Boil remaining water with sugar for 5 minutes to make a syrup.
Add tomatoes, ginger root, lemon and liquid in which lemon was cooked.
Boil until tomatoes are clear and the syrup somewhat thick.
Remove scum.
Fill hot, sterilized jars 3/4 full with the preserved fruit. If paraffin is to be used, add enough syrup to fill jar to 1/4 inch of top of jar; otherwise, fill to top.
Seal, label and store.

title: mexican beef dip
directions: Brown the ground hamburger and drain well. Set the cooking temperature to low. Cut the Velveeta cheese into 1/2 inch blocks (that is just to help melt the cheese faster than if you drop the whole block into the pot).

Add the cheese and continue to stir so the ground meat does not burn. Once the cheese has started to melt, add the salsa. Once the cheese is completely melted, the dip is done! Allow the dip to cool and put in the fridge. (It is better if made the night before!) Put the crock-pot on the day to serve and put on low heat. Watch out because if it simmers in the crock-pot too long it will get very soupy! Serve with tortilla chips.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: *Make sure it's regular mix with no pudding added in cake mix.

title: latija
directions: Slice 12 x 12-inch sponge cake lengthwise and spread on the bottom of a platter.
Place 1 1/3 cups of water in a saucepan; bring it almost to a boil and add milk and sugar.
Mix remaining 1/3 cup of water with cornstarch and vanilla.
Gradually add to the milk mixture, stirring constantly until starch mixture is cooked and there are no lumps.
Remove from heat and add butter. Stir in beaten eggs, 1/4 portion at a time, while stirring vigorously.
Pour latija on top of sponge cake and sprinkle with plenty of cinnamon.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Roll or shake chicken in this and arrange in 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° about 45 minutes. Combine soup with milk, paprika and cheese.
Pour over chicken and bake 30 minutes more.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: genoese minestrone soup
directions: Heat olive oil in large saucepot.
Add garlic, onion and parsley.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, celery, carrots, potatoes, string beans, water and bouillon cubes.
Simmer covered about 1 hour.
Bring to a boil; add cooked macaroni and kidney beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Add flavor packet from noodles.
Pour this over the salad just before serving.

title: mustard meat loaf with celery
directions: Season hamburg; add egg.
Mix well and roll out.
Spread mustard on one side.
Spread sauteed veggies on other side.
Add Parmesan or other type of cheese.
Fold mustard side of hamburg over veggies and seal.
(Disregard cheese over veggies if you don't want the cheese.)
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 15 minutes.
Before done, add canned potatoes to warm them.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Heat oil in a 10-inch nonstick skillet over high heat. Add beef, stirring to break up pieces; cook 3 minutes or until no longer pink. Add 2 cups hot water, milk, green pepper, soup mix, salt and pepper; stir to mix. Scatter pasta over top; cover and bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes, stirring 3 to 4 times with a fork to separate strands of pasta. Stir in peas and carrots; cover, reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes or until vegetables and pasta are tender. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining 1/4 cup hot water. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Dip bottom of glass in water, then in sugar; press top of each cookie to flatten.
Bake at 425° about 5 to 8 minutes or until delicately browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: french raisin pie
directions: Mix and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit ripple cookie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread half of batter to 2/3 of batter on bottom of jelly roll pan.
Top with fruit (I usually use two different kinds like:
1/2 cherry and 1/2 apple).
Drizzle rest of batter on top of fruit filling.
Work in with fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ice cream cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Fill cups approximately 2/3 full.
Place filled cups in a 13 x 9-inch pan and gently place in oven.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Test with toothpick in center.
When completely cool, frost and decorate with sprinkles.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Add milk. Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.

title: western burgers
directions: Brown meat with onion and spices.
Drain and add mustard and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Thaw frozen dinner rolls. Roll out roll and place a spoonful of meat into each roll.
Seal roll and let rise.
Bake until browned following baking directions on package of rolls.

title: corn flakes drops
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly, then fold in remaining ingredients.

title: asparagus, pea casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus spears, garlic salt and onion in buttered casserole.
Mix soup, cheese and peas and pour on top.
Toss together and sprinkle bread and margarine on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly and crumbs are golden.
Serves 6. If you like, you may add a layer of green beans with the asparagus to serve 10.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes without peeling.
Cool, peel and cut into cubes. Add eggs, onion and celery. Coat with salad dressing.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients well. Add milk, then egg yolk.
Mix well and cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, with a whisk. Cook until thick and an indention is left when you stir a spoon through it.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie crust and cover with meringue.
Brown meringue in preheated 425° oven. Cool to room temperature before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: arkansas campfire potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in oil in a large frying pan with lid.
Just before potatoes are done, add remaining ingredients.
Cover pan and steam until potatoes are tender.
Remove lid and let liquid cook away.

title: broccoli and spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute 3 chopped cloves of garlic in olive oil until golden brown.
Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Pour garlic and oil mixture over spaghetti and broccoli. Toss well, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let sit in refrigerator until chilled.

title: stokley's delight
directions: Drain all vegetables and mix together.
Heat remaining ingredients until boiling.
Cool. Pour over vegetables.

title: butter dips
directions: Stir ingredients until dough clings together.
Turn out on floured board to knead.
Pat out then cut into 1-inch strips. Melt 1/2 cup butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dip strips in melted butter and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jello-popcorn
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Pour over popcorn.
Spread on wax paper or form into balls.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Combine ingredients and beat with mixer until very thick and creamy.
Serve over angel food, sponge or any plain cake.
Whip keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: mrs. fred wells' white butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in tube pan or may bake in layers.

title: rabbit stew
directions: Cover rabbits with water in large pan; cook for 2 hours or until meat is easily removed from bones.
Reserve liquid from pan. Debone rabbits; put meat back in pan.
Add liquid and vegetables; bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer until vegetables are done.
Add salt and pepper.
Make paste with flour and water; stir into the mixture to thicken it.
Remove from heat and eat.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: payday cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup margarine and egg together.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan 12 to 18 minutes at 350°.
While still hot put 3 cups marshmallows on top.
Mix and stir on stove until smooth the corn syrup, 1/4 cup margarine, vanilla and chips. Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Pour over crust.
Cool and cut.

title: biscuit mix bread
directions: Add just enough water to mix to make a workable dough.
Knead it a few times to mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Dust loaf with flour.
Place in a large sheet of well-greased heavy-duty foil. Wrap, leaving plenty of room to expand.
Make a small hole for steam to escape.
Place package of dough on grill over edge of coals.
Turn every 5 minutes.
Bread is done when a straw poked through the foil comes out clean, about 15 minutes.
Place in middle of grill last 3 minutes for crunchy crust.
Worth trying a second time if it isn't right the first time!

title: seafood-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat
oven to 375°.
Remove stems from mushrooms and chop finely;
set
aside.
Brush
mushroom caps with 7 tablespoons melted butter;
arrange on lightly greased baking pan. In
small bowl
combine remaining ingredients except 1 tablespoon
butter and
2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Fill each cap with
some
of the mixture.
Combine reserved butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over
stuffed
mushrooms.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 15 to 20 mushroom caps.
A great appetizer!

title: popcorn caramel crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In open roasting pan, combine cereal and popcorn; set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine margarine, sugar, corn syrup and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until mixture is boiling, stirring frequently.
Pour hot mixture over cereal mixture, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on waxed paper to cool, stirring occasionally.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: gudie's wiener schnitzel
directions: Cut steak into 6 serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper. Coat with flour.
Dip into eggs and carefully coat with crumbs. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes to seal coating.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream sugar, butter and salt in medium bowl.
Blend vanilla. Add milk and beat gradually until frosting is spreading consistency.

title: cucumber marinade
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and white onions.
Pour marinade over cucumbers and chill.

title: cream of paresian soup
directions: Mix all together and heat through.
Put in crock-pot to heat if you want.

title: oven baked french fries
directions: Wash and cut potatoes into strips.
Dip into liquid Butter Buds and arrange on baking sheet that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown and turn and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
You may try different seasonings such as garlic powder, onion powder or chili powder.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer bread and drained pineapple.
Mix eggs, sugar and butter.
Pour over bread and pineapple, covering thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously butter a 9 x 13-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
In a large bowl, toss the potatoes with 1/2 cup Gruyere cheese and the flour.

title: sweet potato fritters
directions: Combine butter, potatoes, sugar, milk and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Sift flour; measure and sift with baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep fat (365°).
Fry until brown.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Place chocolate in 2 tablespoons coffee in a saucepan to melt. Add sugar and butter.
Add 1 egg yolk at a time over low heat (use less yolks if more than 4 people).
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add vanilla and mix by folding in chocolate mixture.
Line a deep dish with ladyfingers vertically and on the bottom.
Sprinkle liberally with rum, whiskey or Kahlua.
Pour in mousse. Refrigerate overnight.
You can top with whipped cream, or invert, then top with whipped cream.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and nuts together.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Cover; chill at least 4 hours.
Serve in chilled cups.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Cut up 6 hard-boiled eggs, with salt and pepper to taste. Stir in sufficient quantity of drawn butter, adding, just as you serve, minced onion, parsley and thyme.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place 1 package of rolls in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 C. sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread over dough.
Place second package of rolls over mixture.
Beat egg white with whisk or fork until frothy.
Spread over the top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/2 C. sugar mixture.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Combine milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Add flour.
Wash and cut onions crosswise into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Dip rings one at a time in mixture and fry in deep hot oil (375°). Turn each ring only once so that both sides are very brown.

title: cafe au lait mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. Makes 2 cups mix.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Combine and sift flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Cut in butter until fine as corn meal.
Spread over bottom and halfway up sides of ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Place peaches, cut side up, on mixture.
Combine cinnamon and remaining sugar; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Mix egg yolks and cream; pour over Kuchen and continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add spaghetti sauce.
Cook until hot.
Starting with meat sauce mixture, layer meat sauce, noodles, Ricotta cheese, 1 cup water, meat sauce, noodles, meat sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Cover with waxed paper and aluminum foil; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
During last 5 minutes, uncover and add Mozzarella cheese.

title: pine bark
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with foil.
Place package of saltine crackers in a single layer over the foil.
In a saucepan, melt 1 cup brown sugar and 2 sticks margarine.
Let thicken, then pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes (until bubbly).
Remove from oven and pour the 12 ounce package of milk chocolate morsels over the top.
Place back in oven for 1 to 2 minutes.
Then spread the chocolate over top (like icing).
Let cool in freezer 30 to 60 minutes.
Then break up into pieces.
Store in refrigerator in plastic container.

title: salami
directions: * If beef tallow has already been added, use 18 pounds meat and 5 or 6 pounds pork.

title: spinach and bacon salad
directions: Wash and drain greens.
Break off stems and tear apart. Combine lettuce and spinach.
Drain, cool and crumble bacon.
Add to greens.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt.
Add to the beaten eggs; beat smooth.
Stir in rhubarb.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch lattice top pie.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with rhubarb mixture.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Adjust lattice top; seal.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Use 2-quart baking dish.
Layer zucchini, alternated with sugar and salt.
Layer onions, alternated with sugar and salt. Repeat layers.
Pour tomato sauce over zucchini and onions.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Place desired amount in bake dish and heat in microwave.

title: healthy heart lemon baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray baking pan or casserole dish with vegetable spray (like Pam).
In a small bowl, combine lemon juice, oil and garlic.
Set aside.
Rinse chicken; pat dry. Arrange chicken in prepared pan or dish.
Pour lemon juice mixture over chicken.
I lightly salt my chicken before pouring lemon juice mixture over it, then I sprinkle lightly with lemon pepper. Cover and bake about 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes or longer to brown.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour each ingredient in layers in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat down gently by hand.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into squares.
Eat and enjoy.

title: green and white lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Cook spinach and drain.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine mixed vegetables, softened butter and Cheez Whiz in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased casserole pan.
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook noodles, rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and parsley, Parmesan cheese.
In pan, layer sauce, noodles, cottage cheese mix and Mozzarella cheese and sauce; repeat until gone.
Bake at 375° until bubbling through, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: sausage-cheese appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Use hands.
Make into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet and freeze.
Do not let them touch.
After frozen, place in plastic bag and keep in freezer.
When ready to use, take out what you need and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.
Serve with favorite sauce to dip in (I like J. Lee Roy's Dippin Sauce).

title: gladys' apple sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop sauerkraut finer than in can.
Mix all ingredients and cover tightly.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Very good.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a small bowl combine the peanut butter, honey, powdered milk and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Place cookie crumbs in a shallow bowl.
With hands, shape about 1 teaspoon of mixture into a ball; roll in crumbs.
Place on a large plate.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Makes 42 balls.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Each ball contains 30 calories.

title: chocolate delight bars
directions: Heat chocolate in heavy saucepan over very low heat or microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Beat in cream cheese and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape quickly into 1-inch balls.
Roll in nuts and coconut.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients by hand.
It works best if sausage and cheese are room temperature.
Mix until it makes one large ball. Pull off small chunks and roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 75 balls.

title: chocolate-caramel tortillas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly coat baking sheets with cooking spray.
Stack tortillas; cut into 8 wedges.
Arrange wedges in single layer on prepared cookie sheets.
Lightly spray tops with cooking spray.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes, until golden and crisp. Slide onto wire rack to cool.
Melt chocolate in small pan over low heat.
Put caramels and water in another small pan; stir constantly over low heat until caramels melt.
Working with about 12 at a time, place wedges on a wire rack; drizzle with chocolate and caramel.
Remove to waxed paper to harden.

title: banana coffeecake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in banana.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Put in square greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: art league punch
directions: Blender mix for 1/2 minute the cream of coconut with some of the orange juice.
Place all ingredients in punch bowl and stir well, then add the ice cubes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with crackers or toast points.

title: fruit and honey spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach and fruit. Mix jam, vinegar, honey and olive oil. Stir with whisk. Drizzle dressing over spinach and toss with nuts.

title: meatball stew
directions: Cook onions in oil until tender.
Remove to large bowl and add hamburg, bread, egg, 1/4 cup water, salt and basil.
Shape into balls and brown, removing meatballs as they brown.
In drippings, quickly cook potatoes and carrots until brown.
Return meatballs and add frozen Brussels sprouts, bouillon, 2 cups water and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir flour and 1/4 cup water to thicken.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter. Stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil without stirring 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn. Mix well. Turn on oven at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven and cool. Break apart and store in tightly covered container.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in mixing bowl.
Pour half the batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle half the cheese over batter, then add remaining batter.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of batter.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: zucchini bread no. 1
directions: In a large bowl, stir together all but egg and oil.
Beat eggs and oil together and pour over other mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 2 smaller disposable pans.
Bake at 350° (one loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes clean or two disposable pans for 1 hour or until toothpick comes clean).
Turn out and cool completely.

title: sweet fruit dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion; mix well.
Add oil and vinegar.
Beat with mixer until thick.

title: low calorie onion dip
directions: Blend yogurt and cottage cheese in bowl.
Add onion soup mix; mix well.
Let set, covered, in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Serve with vegetables.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Coat a pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread unpeeled eggplant in pan.
Lightly spray top of eggplant.
Broil until brown.
Preheat oven to 350°. In baking dish, layer tomato-vegetable sauce, eggplant, Mozzarella, sauce, eggplant, Mozzarella and sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan.
Bake covered for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add Karo and mix thoroughly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Put nuts on bottom of pie crust; pour mixture over. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.
When a knife comes out clean, pie is done.

title: vegetarian chili(quick and easy tempeh chili)
directions: Saute tempeh (frozen or thawed) with bulgur wheat and some garlic powder in water until crumbly.
Add water until completely done.
The tempeh absorbs the water quickly.

Add 1 can of sauce, can of water, chili beans and any seasonings (I usually add lots of chili powder and onion powder because that's how we like it) and simmer, uncovered, for about 1/2 hour until slightly thickened. You can also add chopped onion, celery or tomatoes during the simmering time.
Serve over elbow macaroni or brown rice.
Top with chopped onion and/or shredded cheese of your choice.
Serves 6 to 8. (Vegan style recipe if no cheese is added.)
This takes about 1 hour start to finish.

title: squash and zucchini casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to box directions, adding onion soup mix.
Fry hamburg with salt and pepper.
Fry squash and zucchini, onion may be added.
Chop green pepper and tomato.
Mix above together and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 25 - 30 minutes in 350 degree oven until cheese is melted.

title: popcorn soup
directions: Cook corn in 1 cup milk until tender.
Melt margarine and saute onion until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; then additional milk, half and half and cooked corn.
Cook until thickened.
Sprinkle top of soup with popcorn before serving. Serves 4.

title: venison chops
directions: Combine wine, oil onions, garlic, black pepper, and rosemary in a large shallow dish, mixing well.
Add venison chops. Marinate in refrigerator for 3 to 12 hours, turning occasionally. Drain and discard the marinade.
Heat a large skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray over high heat.
Add the chops.
Sear the chops on both sides; reduce the heat.
Add the country ham.
Cook over medium-low heat until the ham is of desired doneness. Arrange the ham on warmed serving plates.
Top with venison chops.

title: bob's smokey bbq beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°f. 190°c. gas mark 5. Fry the bacon until crisp and saute the onion in 2 Tbsp. bacon drippings until tender. Add bacon and remaining ingredients including bean juice. Put in a 2 qt. casserole and bake for 30 minutes or until bubbling. Makes 8 x 1/2 cup servings.

title: fiesta pralines
directions: Mix all but vanilla; bring to a boil.
Boil by clock 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat till creamy, 1 to 2 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Work fast!
Cool and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix and cook first 5 ingredients in enough water to cover for approximately 30 minutes.
Cover with lid.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and milk and return to heat.
Mix flour with enough warm water to make a paste and pour into soup mixture.
This thickens enough to be hearty and warming.

title: tomato salsa
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the tomatoes, onion, peppers and vinegar.
Cover tightly and chill in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour to blend flavors before serving.

title: orange tube cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add buttermilk, alternating with flour, soda, salt and baking powder. Add orange rind. Bake 1 hour in tube pan at 325°.

title: fruit salad
directions: *Stir in some lemon juice to preserve color.

title: fresh frozen dessert
directions: Stir all ingredients together and freeze.
Delicious!

title: charlotte's hot and sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles and discard
pickle juice.
Place pickles in large mixing bowl.	Slice and layer in jar 3 pickles, 2 or 3 peppers, garlic clove and 1 cup sugar.
Repeat layers in jar. Shake each day for one week.

title: zucchini meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine hamburg, zucchini, bread crumbs and seasonings.
(Mixture will be very wet.)
Shape into 6 mini meat loaves.
Place in a baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Brush on additional chili sauce on the tops of meat loaves.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: mexican bake
directions: Boil noodles according to directions on bag.
Drain well. Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except the cheese.
Put in two 11 x 13 pans.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove foil and add cheese and bake uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: caramels
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add syrup and milk, stir constantly until it boils and stir occasionally.
Cook until it forms a firm ball in cold water (247° to 250° or firm ball stage). Add nuts and pour into buttered pan.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Toss with chicken mixture.
Cover and chill for several hours.
(Light mayonnaise may be used.)

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: darn good chocolate cake
directions: **Or dark chocolate fudge cake mix.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Mix above together and enjoy.

title: chinese walnuts
directions: Boil walnuts for 2 minutes.
Place in strainer and rinse with warm water.
Place walnuts in a bowl and sprinkle the sugar over them.
Toss until the walnuts are all covered with sugar.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine and spread evenly in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Spread ingredients in order listed above in layers over margarine. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and devein raw shrimp; press center with thumb to fan over medium flame.
Melt butter in large skillet; add garlic; add shrimp.
Cook and stir until pink and firm (about 10 to 12 minutes).
Add parsley and wine; simmer approximately 2 minutes.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Make crust by combining flour, salt and baking powder with shortening.
Add water and stir.
Turn dough onto floured surface and divide into 2 parts.
Roll out each part as thin as possible and spread with uncooked sausage.
Roll into long roll (like jelly roll) and slice.
Place slices onto cookie sheet; bake 20 to 25 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 50.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Beat together and set aside the eggs, milk and flour.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Layer cheese, chilies and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done. (Knife inserted comes out clean.)

title: nutty noodles
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in a large iron skillet over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; quickly stir in noodles and nuts until evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill.

title: blackberry squares
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Sift all dry ingredients in a bowl. Cut in cheese, sugar and butter with a pastry blender.
Take out 3/4 cup crumbs and set aside.
Add milk to remaining crumbs; stir and press into pan.
Spread layer of jam and sprinkle 3/4 cup crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
For different taste, try 1/2 cup raspberry jam and 1/2 cup strawberry jam in place of blackberry jam.

title: turnip au gratin
directions: Combine turnips, salt and sugar in a saucepan.
Add water to cover, bring to a boil then simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and milk until thickened and bubbly.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Fold in drained turnips.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart slightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 layer cakes.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use powdered sugar as icing.

title: peas and bacon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in bowl and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: Add onion, green pepper, beef and rice to hot oil.
Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring quickly to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer for 25 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, cloves and salt. Stir in butter, water and molasses until well blended. Pour into pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes, until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool slightly on warm rack. Serve warm with Lemon Sauce.

title: do ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and mash with the remaining ingredients.
Place the mixture in a greased casserole.
Dot with butter and cover. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler. Add milk; cook 5 minutes over boiling water, stirring constantly. Remove from fire and add water and vanilla. Allow to cool before putting into baked pie shell. Top with Cool Whip or whip cream.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine cake mix and Jell-O in a bowl.
Add water and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each one.
Add oil, mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
After cake is done, immediately punch holes in cake and pour all the lemon frosting all over it.

title: baked catfish
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, Parmesan cheese, paprika, salt and black pepper.
Set aside.
Whisk together egg white and milk.
Dip fillets in milk mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place on a foil-lined baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Coat each fillet lightly with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: grandma irwin's ham casserole
directions: Great day after Easter meal.

title: stars and stripes dessert
directions: Slice 1 cup of the strawberries; set aside.
Save remaining strawberries; set aside.
Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish with 8 slices of cake.

Top with one cup of sliced strawberries, one cup blueberries, then the whipped topping. Place strawberry halves and remaining 1/3 cup blueberries over topping to create a flag design or garnish as desired. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Make into rounded teaspoonful size balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in airtight container for at least 3 weeks.
If necessary, roll bourbon balls again in confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid.
Melt butter in pan, adding flour and onion.
Cook slowly and add broccoli liquid, stirring until smooth.
Add seasonings and cheese.
When cheese melts, add broccoli.
Put in shallow casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6. Can be made day ahead and refrigerated until baked.

title: white wine sangria
directions: Stir together white wine, orange juice, sugar, lime juice and brandy until sugar dissolves.
Add fruit and refrigerate.
Add club soda before serving with ice cubes.

title: shrimp ratatouille
directions: Cut shrimp in half lengthwise.
In a large skillet, saute zucchini, eggplant, onion, green pepper and mushrooms in oil for 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Add shrimp, stirring frequently for about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, garlic salt, basil, parsley and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until shrimp are tender.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma mary's raisin pie
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, water, syrup and raisins.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes more. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and margarine.
Pour filling into pastry lined pie plate glass pie dish; filling will be thin.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 375° and bake 30 minutes more or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburger and noodle
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain grease.
Cook noodles.
Add a dash of salt and mushroom soup.
Mix together hamburger, noodles, mushroom soup, bell pepper and can of water.
Put in oven and cook for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican nachos
directions: Place tortilla chips on a plate and top with cheeses. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Rotate place and cook for an additional 1 minute.
Serve immediately.

title: party ham sandwiches
directions: Slice rolls in half sandwich style.
Spread honey-mustard on rolls, then layer ham and cheese.
Heat the remaining ingredients and pour over the top of sandwiches.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Slice and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and put into a well-greased Pyrex dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes.
Makes a large casserole.

title: cheesy drop biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: texas steak strips
directions: Cut meat into even strips.
Heat half margarine and cook meat until done.
Remove meat and keep warm.
Add remaining margarine to pan.
Add green onions and saute 4 or 5 minutes until soft, but not brown.
Remove.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Store 12 hours, covered.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: nutty chex mix recipe
directions: In a large skillet, combine oil and peanut butter. Stir over low heat until smooth. Remove from heat. Blend in seasoning. Add Chex and nuts.
Mix until pieces are well coated.
Heat over low heat for 10 minutes until Chex are crisp. Stir continuously. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Yields 6 3/4 cups.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Marinate chops overnight in sauce and grill.
When done, put pineapple slices on top.

title: creamy cheese fondue
directions: With electric mixer, add milk to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Heat slowly in saucepan.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and garlic salt.
Slowly add cheese, stirring until smooth.
Pour into fondue pot; place over fondue burner.
If mixture thickens too much, add a little milk.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together the flour, butter and powdered sugar until crumbly and press in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crab imperial
directions: In a skillet, cook onion and butter until tender but not brown.
Stir drained mushrooms into large mixing bowl with butter and onion mix.
Add crabmeat, crackers, parsley, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix completely and put in baking dish (approximately 12 x 6 x 1-inch).
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes; brown in broiler for 5 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, starting with smallest ingredient first.
Use 1/3 cup dry mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape and roll in pecans.

title: punch
directions: You may crush the strawberries if you wish.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir and mix well.
Enjoy!

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze hard.
Take out and put in punch bowl.
Mix with ginger ale.
This will thaw fast.
It can be kept frozen 1 month to 6 weeks.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Cut carrots into bite-size pieces.
Quarter onion.
Mix the above with the rest of the ingredients and stir well.
May be baked in oven at 250° for 5 or 6 hours or cooked in a slow cooker all day.
Serve over rice.

title: mom's chili con carne
directions: Brown ground meat and drain off grease.
Lightly saute onion and pepper.
Put meat, onion, pepper and all other ingredients (except cornstarch and water) into large Dutch oven type pan. Cover and cook over medium to low heat, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour.
If mixture is too soupy, mix cornstarch and water in a small bowl and add to chili mixture.
Continue cooking a few minutes, stirring to let cornstarch thicken the mixture.
Serve steaming hot.

title: pineapple cream cheese coffeecake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs, and 1 c. pineapple juice. (Reserve 2 Tbsp pineapple for later use.)
Beat with hand mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add can drained pineapple.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar, almond extract and the 2 Tbsp. pineapple.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 cake pan.
Pour in cake batter.
Drop cream cheese mixture evenly over batter by tablespoon.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix all in large pot.
Boil slowly for about 30 minutes, or until onions are cooked (transparent).
If you do not have jalapeno peppers, use 3 long red peppers or 1/4 teaspoon red pepper.
Pour while hot into sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 2 to 3 pints.
Use on cold cuts and scrambled eggs.

title: pepper kakor-swedish ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour; add flour gradually.
Dough will be very stiff.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 2 1/2 to 3-inch circles.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: one pot supper
directions: Brown chops in a skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: aunt sue's banana pudding custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Heat milk in double boiler. Beat flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Then stir into scalded milk.
Cook until thickened.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Put into casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs mixed with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: uncle charles' corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased pan that is 9 x 12-inch.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Mix and pour the remaining ingredients into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Pie can be baked with no top crust or you may add a crisscross top for decoration before baking.

title: mother's meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Shape into loaf pan and top with catsup or chili sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine with chocolate (broken in pieces) in a double boiler or small pan, stirring often.
In mixer, beat eggs slightly; add sugar mixed with flour.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add chocolate and margarine mixture; beat 1 minute more. Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Cover with whipped cream. Can shave 3 tablespoons German chocolate and sprinkle on top. Refrigerate before serving.

title: green bean casserole(microwave for 18 minutes.)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, crumble beef; add onion.
Cook at High for 5 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Drain off excess fat.
Add salt and pepper. Stir in beans and soup.
Set aside.

title: boston scrod
directions: Season the fish fillets with salt and pepper and place them on a broiler tray.
Brush with butter and broil for about 5 minutes. Combine remaining butter with breadcrumbs, mustard, onion salt, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, lemon juice and parsley.
Spoon the mixture carefully on top of each fish fillet, covering it completely.
Press down lightly to pack the crumbs into place. Broil for a further 5 to 7 minutes, or until the top is lightly browned and the fish flakes.

title: avocado-shrimp salad
directions: Cut avocados lengthwise into halves.
Remove pit and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Boil shrimp.
Cut into pieces and combine with celery.
Add rest of ingredients.
Fill centers of avocados and serve on lettuce.

title: beans and greens
directions: Coarse-chop escarole and simmer in broth.
Saute garlic, peppers and oregano in oil and butter in separate pan.
Add beans and wine.
Simmer beans 5 minutes.
Combine beans with broth. Stir and serve with Romano cheese, if desired.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Combine sugar, spices and salt. Mix with apples.
Fill crust.
On top of apples, put butter and flour, crumbled together.
(Can put another crust on top of apples.)
Make holes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cook 50 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.
Place cookie sheet under pie to cook crust better.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat off.
Add all the rest of ingredients. Mix well and put into casserole.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook on medium heat until thick and clear.
Add box of Jell-O.
Remove from stove and mix well; add slices of peaches and let cool.
Pour in 10-inch pie shell.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve with topping.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles.
Cut all vegetables into small bite size.
Mix noodles, vegetables, tomatoes and olives.
Add Italian dressing. Mix together and add about half the bottle of Salad Supreme.
Top with grated cheese (optional).
Tastes great, warm or chilled.

title: smoked venison roast
directions: Marinate roast in liquid smoke for 1 hour.
Take roast out of marinade and sprinkle pepper all over.
Then pat pepper into roast with your hand.
Wrap roast with several strips of smoked bacon. Prepare smoker to manufacturer's instructions.
When coals ash over, fill drip pan with water.
Liberally cover coals with hickory chunks.
Put roast on smoker and cook 1 1/2 hours per pound.
Better when served the next day.

title: cincinnati skyline chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Put meat and onion in crock-pot (4-quart). Add the rest of the ingredients. Cook slowly, covered, 4 to 5 hours. Remove bay leaves before serving. Serve on cooked spaghetti with shredded cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken; cut in chunks and layer in casserole dish.
Stir together sour cream and chicken soup; pour over chicken.
Melt butter.
Add crackers (crushed) and poppy seed.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Thaw Cool Whip and cake.
Chop cake into cubes (1/2 of cake for family of five).
Place cubes into large clear serving bowl or small individual serving cups.
Pour chocolate syrup over cake. Crumble peanut butter cups on top of cake.
Mix 6 ounces Cool Whip with pudding (follow instructions on pudding box).
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Combine the lemonade concentrate, pineapple, and strawberries in blender. Blend until smooth. Chill until serving time. Add the ginger ale just before serving.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix grape jelly and mustard over medium heat until dissolved. Cut up wieners into bite sizes and put into jelly mixture.
Heat and serve.
This is also good to put over ham.
Kids love the wieners.

title: vegetable pasta soup
directions: Mix broth, basil and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium.
Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni; cook on low heat for 10 minutes or until macaroni is done, stirring often.
Add vegetables and simmer for 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pina coladas
directions: Stir or shake for 1 minute or in blender, mix 1/2 minute at high speed.
Pour into prechilled glasses.
Serve with pineapple spear.
Yields 2 servings.

title: broccoli-chicken-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package, drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs and melted margarine and using only 1/2 can of Cheddar cheese soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 can of cheese soup.
Mix crushed crackers and melted margarine with fork. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: smoked turkey salad
directions: In large serving bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients except cayenne.
Pour dressing over salad, mix lightly and season with cayenne. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: cow chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream together shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all together in large bowl and add rolled oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Dip with ice cream scoop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Edges will be brown and centers soft.

title: rocky road fudge sauce
directions: Stir together the chips, marshmallow cream and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Serve over ice cream or cake.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy (stiff).
Add sugar gradually. Add vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Spoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Can add food coloring.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Cut into strips. Brown in butter.
Add onion and garlic.
Brown.
Add chicken soup, water and mushrooms.
Simmer, uncovered, until meat is tender, about 20 minutes.
Add sour cream; simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients
and pour over meat.
Cook in covered pan at 350° for six hours.
Shred meat with fork.

title: pumpkin truffle
directions: Mix pumpkin, vanilla, butterscotch pudding and milk together. Layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip and nuts.

title: molasses oat cookies
directions: Place flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and ginger in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix at low speed of mixer until blended, about one minute.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar and shortening; beat until light.
Add eggs and molasses and continue to beat until light.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and spices.
Mix until mixture leaves sides of bowl (you may need to add a little more flour).
Roll dough into walnut sized balls; roll into sugar to coat.
Place on ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart and bake 12 to 14 minutes (shorter for soft cookie and longer for crisp) at 350°.
Cool on racks.
Dough and/or cookies freeze very well.
Makes a bazillion cookies.

title: kentucky cream pull candy
directions: Combine sugar, soda, salt and boiling water.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Put lid on for 2 to 3 minutes to dissolve sugar crystals.
Uncover and do not stir again.
Increase heat to medium and boil to 236°.
Begin adding cream and butter, a small amount at a time.
Do not let temperature fall below 236°.
Boil to 257°. Pour immediately onto a buttered marble slab.
Pull until white. Shape into a rope and cut into small pieces with scissors.
Put into tin container.
Candy will cream overnight.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup brown sugar and salt; gradually add scalded milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add small amount to egg yolks; stir into hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla; cool slightly.
Pour into baked pastry shell; cool.

title: banana split
directions: Layer pineapple, bananas, Dream Whip, nuts and cherries in given order.
Prepare and refrigerate overnight.

title: porcupine meatballs(serves approximately 6)
directions: Mix everything, except soup; form into large meatballs.
Brown in pan on top of stove on all sides; drain.
Add soup and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Yummy!!!

title: apple strudel
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well with hands; make a ball and chill.
Spread 3/4 of dough on a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Arrange sliced apples on dough; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Roll remaining dough; cut in strips and arrange in crisscross across apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Drizzle with confectioners sugar glaze:

title: white cake icing
directions: Combine sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Heat over high heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Reduce heat; boil 3 minutes.
Do not stir.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Pour 2/3 of syrup over egg whites, beating constantly.
Boil remaining syrup 5 minutes.
Pour over egg whites. Beat until desired consistency is reached.
Add vanilla and food coloring.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Mix in the soup out of the can.
Mix in tuna.
Microwave peas until cooked, then add to mixture.
Warm casserole on top of stove.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine 1 egg, Parmesan and butter.
Add spaghetti and toss to coat.
Turn into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Press mixture against bottom and sides to form an even crust.
In a small bowl, combine remaining egg and cottage cheese.
Spread over spaghetti crust.
Set aside.
In skillet, brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook until heated.
Spoon meat mixture over cottage cheese layer.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350°
oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and bake 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve in wedges.

title: chutney cheese spread
directions: Mix room temperature cream cheese with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Transfer to platter and flatten like a pancake.
Just before serving, spread with chutney and top with chopped scallions.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese slice on each and spoon soup over the top.
Sprinkle crumbs over the top and drizzle with melted butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 25 minutes.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter. Add chicken, cooking until no longer pink.
Add pasta and vegetables with water.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp and tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour over corn flakes; mix well and pour in pan.
Press well; cut in squares while warm.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
In a large bowl, beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla at medium speed of mixer for 3 or 4 minutes until well blended.
Add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt or pound cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire rack 20 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Add all the other ingredients.
Mix together and heat in oven until bubbly. Remove from oven.

title: fantasy creamy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring to prevent scorching. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate until melted. Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla. Beat until well blended and stiff. Pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan. Cool at room temperature.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar, soda, flour and salt.
Stir until blended.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail.
Stir by hand until well mixed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Over top sprinkle brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: fettuccine and scallops with wine sauce
directions: Thaw scallops, if frozen.
Cut any large scallops in half.

title: one pot dinner (slow cooker)
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Place in a slow cooker.
Brown the bacon and onions together.
Drain fat; add bacon and onions to slow cooker along with remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 4 to 9 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses all together.
Add dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Roll into ball and cover with chopped nuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and beef.
Add to cream cheese.
Mix well and shape into ball.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Slice potatoes.
Mix with seasoning, cream sauce and dots of butter.
Place in layers in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake slowly for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly touched.
Serve warm.

title: corny cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 400° until top is brown.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pie shells for 5 minutes.
Fill crust with seafood, shrimp, then crab meat.
Sprinkle cheese and onion over seafood.

title: aunt sanny's fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and mix.
Melt oleo and chocolate together.
Add to other mixture.
Stir in milk, salt and vanilla.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of uncooked pie shell.
Pour mixture over this.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: odessa's coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add coconut, butter, sugar and flour.
Add cream. Divide evenly into four pie crusts*.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Let sugar and corn syrup heat on stove until it begins to boil.
Turn off.
Add peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Add corn flakes.
Shape into ball and let cool.

title: baked potato sticks(makes 6 servings)
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into lengthwise strips as for French fries.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, parsley, onion and pepper.
Pour cream over.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; bake in 425° oven for 50 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease rectangular baking dish (13 x9 x 2-inch).
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured board.
Knead 5 times. Roll dough into rectangle, 14 x 10-inch. Place dough in dish so edges are 1/2 inch up sides.

title: wedding soup
directions: Place chicken broth in large pot.
Add onions, carrots, celery, spinach and chicken.
While bringing to a simmer, make small meatballs from meatball mix.
Add to soup along with grated cheese.
Add bouillon cubes if a stronger chicken flavor is desired.
Pepper to taste.
Cook everything together until carrots, celery and onions are done, approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set overnight.
Serve with crackers on lettuce.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a well-buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good served with scoop of ice cream.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix water, cornstarch and vinegar.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Reduce heat and stir after it comes to a boil.
Stir in sugar, butter, grated lemon rind and egg yolks.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool. Beat 3 egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vinegar.

title: hungarian palacsintas
directions: Mix batter as for pancakes, lump free. Let stand 15 minutes or overnight.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Saute chopped onion in fat.
Add to meat which has been placed in mixing bowl.
Add egg, seasoning and washed rice; mix well. Set meat mixture aside while preparing cabbage.
Slice cabbage into slivers or wedges of approximately 1/2 to 1-inch.
Remove any pieces of hard vein from cut pieces.
Place 1/2 of cabbage in large pot.
Form meat into approximately 8 balls of equal size. Place on top of cabbage in pot and cover with remaining cabbage. Pour tomato puree over cabbage and add water to cover.
Cook over low heat for at least 1 hour.

title: marvelous marbled brownies
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter or margarine and sugar in small mixer bowl and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, flour and vanilla and blend well.
Set this mixture aside.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix box of yellow cake mix as the directions give on the box. Pour in a long pan.
After cake is done, punch holes in cake while still warm.
Mix condensed milk and cream of coconut together. Pour on top of cake.
Let cake cool.
Put Cool Whip on top with frozen coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: ratatouille
directions: Prepare cubed eggplant (pare if desired).
Prepare sliced zucchini.
Cook all ingredients in 12-inch skillet over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender.
Makes 6 servings, 140 calories per serving.
Delicious served hot or cold.

title: cookie pizza("a real hit with teens and very easy!")
directions: Combine the butter, sugar and brown sugar; beat until fluffy. Add the egg, vanilla and flour; beat well.
Spread dough evenly into an ungreased pizza pan.

Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Take out and sprinkle hot cookie with the mini marshmallows, the chocolate chips and peanuts or walnuts (coconut is optional). Return to oven; bake 5 more minutes, or until marshmallows are light brown.
Cool, cut into wedges and serve.

title: french pudding cake
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over medium heat until thickened. Set aside to cool.
In large flat dish, put 1/2 of vanilla wafers in bottom.
Put a layer of 1/2 egg mixture, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 pecans.
Repeat and garnish with cherries, coconut and pecans.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix soup, water and lemon juice.
Put on meat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes or until real good and tender.
Add peppers and cook 15 minutes longer.
Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions. Cool cake completely.
Mix both boxes of pudding with milk.
When thick, add liqueur and blend until smooth.
Crush Heath bars into small pieces.

title: ginger dressing
directions: Cut onion and celery into small pieces.
Blend all ingredients in blender or processor at medium speed for 2 minutes. Refrigerate.
Will keep 1 week.
Makes 3 cups.

title: potluck pan rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/2 cup water. Add butter, eggs, powdered milk, salt, 3 cups flour and remaining sugar and water. Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes or until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.

title: blueberries in the snow
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 10 x 14-inch pan.
In a large bowl mix together Cool Whip and sour cream; do not overbeat.
Break cake into 1 inch chunks and fold into 2/3 of Cool Whip and sour cream mixture.
Spread this back into 10 x 14-inch pan and cover with remaining 1/3 of Cool Whip and sour cream mixture.
Top with blueberry pie filling or your favorite fruit pie filling.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Spread margarine lightly over the bread.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
Spoon sausage over bread slices.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: orange punch
directions: Fill ice trays with orange drink and freeze.
Mix rest of drink with ginger ale.
Float orange ice cubes and orange peel on top.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good with carrots, cauliflower, broccoli and other fresh vegetables.
Delicious with potato chips.

title: cornflake christmas wreaths
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter together.
When melted, add vanilla.
Add food coloring to desired color. Mix in cornflakes until all cornflakes are well coated.
Drop in little piles on wax paper.
Add red hots to liking.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix 3 1/2 cups flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Set aside. Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs, water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Add nuts.
Make rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown onion and ground beef together; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until cabbage is done.

title: pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Then, add egg yolks and mix well. Add stiffly beaten egg whites, pineapple and pecans; blend well. Use rolling pin to crush vanilla wafers; reserve part of them for top.
Put layer of crumbs in bottom of pan.
Add pineapple mixture and sprinkle top with remaining crumbs.
Sprinkle a little of the pineapple juice over top to moisten the crumbs.

title: quick ice cream
directions: Freeze banana without skin.
Mix all ingredients in blender. Can add nuts, pecans, cereal, chocolate, vanilla, strawberries, peaches, pineapple or any other flavor desired.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt 1/4 cup margarine and 6 ounces chips in double boiler or over low heat.
Pour over pressed mixture.
Let cool.
Eat!

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Put apple in blender to chop.
Mix jello with 1 cup of hot water.
Put cranberries in blender along with jello mixture, lemon juice and orange peel.
Mix well.
Put in mold and refrigerate. Leave overnight and serve next day.

title: cream cheese bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan; cream together margarine, butter and sugar until light.
Beat in cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in vanilla, then eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and salt.
Spoon into pan and put in cold oven.
Turn oven on to 275° and bake until tester comes out clean, about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Check for doneness after 1 hour.
Allow to cool and remove from pan.
Serve with Blueberry Cinnamon Syrup or dust with confectioners sugar. Serves 8 or more.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thaw strawberries and do not drain.
Put peaches, undrained pineapple, undrained strawberries and bananas in a large bowl in this order.
Mix pudding and Tang together and sprinkle over top of fruit.
Mix gently and refrigerate.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and salt.
Beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat well; add vanilla.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.

title: dutch oven cobbler
directions: Heat charcoal (32 briquettes).
Wash out 2 Dutch ovens.
Place 8 briquettes under each oven and 8 briquettes on each lid.
Warm ovens 5 minutes.
Place 2 cans of pie filling in each oven. Sprinkle one box of cake mix on each.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add 6 pads butter to each and bake 45 minutes.

title: rutabagas
directions: Wash, pare and cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices or cubes. Cook in boiling, salted water until tender.
Season to taste.

title: chocolate crackers
directions: You will need a nonstick cookie sheet with sides.

title: crab quiche
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pie shell.
Bake shell at 450° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Beat together eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Combine cheese, flour and crab.
Sprinkle evenly in pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until tip of knife inserted 1-inch from center comes out clean.
Let stand awhile before cutting. (Excellent reheated.)

title: broccoli salad
directions: Trim large leaves of broccoli and remove tough stalks.
Wash well and cut flowerets and stems into bite size pieces.
Place in large bowl and add crumbled bacon, onions and raisins.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour dressing over broccoli and toss.
Cover and let set in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serve cold.

title: chili
directions: Saute meat and onions until soft; pour off grease.
Add all other ingredients except beans. Simmer 30 minutes.
Rinse beans and add to mixture.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Cut cabbage up fine.
Add bell pepper, onion and one cup sugar.
Sprinkle
over
and work in cabbage, then heat the oil, salt,
celery
seed, tablespoon sugar, dry mustard and vinegar. Pour over other ingredients.
Can be stored in refrigerator.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat after each addition.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt three times.
Add alternately with milk, then add bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: So I substituted rice.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter, mixing well.
Press into spring-form pan, reserving 1/4 cup for topping.
Add creme de menthe to Marshmallow Creme, mixing until blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Freeze for at least 10 hours.

title: granny's cracker candy
directions: Cook for 4 minutes the sugar and milk after they come to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until blended, then stir in crackers.
Pour into a buttered cake pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and bake the cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut in squares and layer as follows:
cake, pudding, blueberry pie filling, cake, pudding, cherry pie filling, cake, pudding and sprinkle pineapple over the pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and cool for 2 hours.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Blend water, butter and cocoa in saucepan and heat to boiling.
Add flour, sugar, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Stir in eggs and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes, no longer.
Spread frosting.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving fantail if you like.
Split shrimp down the back and remove vein.
Mix milk, eggs, baking powder and vinegar together.
Put shrimp in the mixture and let them marinate for 1 hour.
Remove shrimp from mixture, then season with salt and pepper, or your favorite seasoning.
Dip shrimp in flour mix and fry at 380° in oil until light golden brown. (Do not overcook.)

title: peau de creme(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Place chips, sugar, salt, vanilla and coffee in blender (while milk is heating) and blend thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending between and after then slowly add hot milk while blending on high.
Blend 2 minutes more.
Pour into peau de creme pots, tiny wine glasses or demitasse cups.
Serve chilled, topped with whipped cream, if desired.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
While hot, punch holes in top of cake.
Mix condensed milk and caramel topping together.
Pour over cake.
Top with crushed Heath bars.

title: turkey sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together, make into patties and fry in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Serve with grits and eggs.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots thin and cook until tender; drain.
Mix onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients together while carrots are cooking.
Drain carrots and add to mixture; let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Freezes well and lasts in refrigerator a long time.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° in a loaf pan or 9 x 9-inch pan about 1 1/4 hours.
Top with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating real good after each one.
Add flavorings.
Add flour alternately with milk, ending with flour. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until tested done with a wooden pick.
This makes a big cake so use a big tube pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9-inch baking pan. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: killer canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients to smooth consistency and spread on small rounds or squares of rye bread.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Brown meat in pan.
Stir in soup mix and water.
Cook 2 hours. Add vegetables and cook 45 minutes.
Remove meat and vegetables. Add 1/4 cup water and flour, stir until smooth.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Crisco; cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add flour and milk, alternating; mix well.
Add flavorings and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk and sugar in a large heavy saucepan or Dutch Oven. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.

Cook to a boil; cover, boil 5 min. and turn off heat. Add marshmellows, stir until melted. Add the 3 kinds of chocolate, one at a time, stirring until melted. Add vanilla and nuts, blend. Pour into buttered 10x15 inch pan.
Let stand until firm before cutting. Top with nuts if desired.

title: jiffy crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix the cream and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving a little stuffing for topping.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: christmas butter toffee
directions: Rim top of 8-cup batter bowl with butter, then place butter, sugar, salt and water in the bowl.
Microwave on Full power 7 to 8 minutes, then microwave on Full power 30 seconds at a time to the color brown or gold you want.
Line a cookie sheet with tinfoil and lay nuts on sheet.
When mixture is done, pour over nuts slowly, then wait for it to cool.
Break in smaller pieces and put into waxed paper lined gift boxes.

title: derby mint juleps
directions: Pull off bottom leaves of long stemmed mint.
Crush and drop in pitcher.
Add bourbon.
Meanwhile, mix sugar and water syrup making a thick consistency; add lemon juice.
Use 2 teaspoons syrup for each ounce of whiskey.
Stir as you go.
When right taste, pour 2 to 3 ounces in bottom of each glass and pack tightly with crushed ice.
Stir vigorously until glass is frosted.
Sprig mint, pinching mint to make smell good!
Then, sit back, relax and sip on your "Julep" while you bet on the horse of your choice!
Good Luck!

title: mandarin orange fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add oranges and pineapple with juices.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cool and chill until firm.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Add cheese.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Melt butter.
Cut fish.
Season with spices and onions, then the soup.
Add crushed crackers and melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut meringue
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Spray oven dish with nonstick spray.
Pour mix into oven dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°; check regularly with knife.
If knife clean, coconut is ready.
Do not overcook.
Beat egg whites with 12 tablespoons of sugar until it hardens.
Spread whites over cake; place back in oven for 5 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Remove; cool for 30 minutes. Pour Hershey's syrup over top; cut into squares.

title: veggie bites
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in soup, broccoli and cheese until well mixed.
Refrigerate 20 minutes.
Roll out pastry to 11 x 11 inches.
Ease pastry into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Prick bottom with a fork.
Spoon broccoli mixture into pan.
Fold pastry edges toward center.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, until center is set. Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: garlic dressing salad
directions: Blend ingredients in bowl with electric mixer on high speed. Blend well.

title: creamed chicken and vegetable soup
directions: Boil chicken in 1 1/2 quarts water with onion, salt and pepper until tender; cool.
In soup pot, melt oleo and add carrots, celery and cabbage in that order.
Cover and steam until vegetables are soft.
Add 1 quart chicken broth and potatoes. Simmer until vegetables are soft.
Add cheese, cubed.
Heat until cheese melts.
Use as much of chicken breast as desired; chop fine and add to soup.
Use other meat for another dish.
Serves 4.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In bowl mix both flours together.
In another large bowl, mix all other ingredients together.
Add to flour mixture.
Knead well.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double. Work down good, put in greased loaf pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: midnight cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Blend in well beaten eggs. Combine hot water and cocoa.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into two greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, onion, bacon and cheese in large bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise; stir well.
Pour over broccoli mixture and stir.
If not enough to coat well, make another 1/2 batch of mayonnaise mixture.

title: box oven
directions: Completely
line
the
inside
of the box with aluminum foil, shiny
side
out.
Secure the foil to the box with tape. To use oven, place
a
piece of foil on the ground
that is a little wider
and	longer	than the box.
Make sure the box is level. Set
the
soda cans on the foil and make sure they are stable. Put the rack on top of the cans.
Place coals on foil on the ground.
Place
item to be baked on the rack and cover with foil-lined box.
Make sure 1 corner of the box is propped up with a small rock to keep coals going.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add flour slowly.
Add vanilla and nuts, mix well.
Shape into size of fingers.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: cinnamon popover dounuts
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Drop into hot oil.

title: chicken monte carlo
directions: Simmer chicken 1 hour in onion salted water.
Skin, bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Next, add chicken pieces.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and then herb dressing.
Drizzle margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: italian lemon chicken
directions: In a large broiling pan, place chicken, garlic, cut-up wedges of potatoes and olive oil and bake until brown.
Add lemon juice, water, parsley, then salt and pepper to taste.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and place in a baking pan that has been sprayed with a vegetable spray.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kielbasa medley
directions: Cook sausage until brown and done.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat until potatoes are done.
If desired, top with Cheddar cheese.

title: beef with mushroom gravy
directions: Place beef in a large casserole and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine soup, water, soup mix, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Stir and heat through.
Pour over beef. Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250°. Bake 2 hours longer or until beef is tender.

title: crab and artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour, add milk gradually. Cook on low, stirring constantly until thickened.
