Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire, cheese, mustard, eggs, artichokes, mushrooms and crab meat. Pour into buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan and bread crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add and mix other ingredients, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before cutting.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Add cream cheese; let melt.
Add cottage cheese; let cool.
Add pineapple and fold in whipped cream.
Let set until firm.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs and cocoa.
Mix until mixture is creamy.
Add salt and flour to mixture, mixing well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Coat top of brownies with chocolate glaze, if desired.

title: caramel apples
directions: You will need 3 craft sticks and aluminum foil to roll them in.

title: coconut brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Open can and add one can water. Simmer until it boils.

title: kentucky coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot and green pepper in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar, vinegar and salt; bring to a boil and boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Cool.
Stir celery seed and mustard seed into vinegar mixture.
Pour over vegetables, stirring well.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Yields about 5 quarts.
Slaw may be stored several weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Cut up 1/2 cake.
Place in bottom of large bowl.
Sprinkle 1/2 Kahlua over cake.
Pour on 1/2 pudding; add 1 container Cool Whip. Sprinkle on 1/2 Brickle.
Repeat layers all over again. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: stir-fry vegetables and rice
directions: In a large heavy skillet or wok, stir-fry carrots, cabbage and broccoli for 3 minutes on medium heat in oil.
Add rest of vegetables; continue to stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add rice and soy sauce.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cut butter and cheese into flour and baking powder with a pastry blender.
Add water and mix well.
Fill cookie press.
Form straws.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes; cut while hot into desired lengths.
Cool.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Add flour to melted butter.
Add milk and heat on stove for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Add cheese and mix.
Heat on stove again until cheese has melted.
Add onions and salt and pepper if you desire.

title: baked fish
directions: Wash and pat fish dry.
Place in baking dish.
Pour remaining ingredients over fish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Combine sugar and oil in large bowl; mix well.
Add carrots and blend eggs in, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add dry ingredients; blend in nuts.
Bake in ungreased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake 1 package of yellow cake mix according to directions on package in 13 x 13-inch pan.
Heat pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Pour over warm cake.
Slice bananas over pineapple. Make up pudding according to package and pour over bananas. Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Mix coconut and pecans.
Sprinkle over top of Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: porcupine meatballs(crock-pot)
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, onion, green pepper, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into meatballs about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place meatballs in crock-pot.
Pour soup over mixture.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: mom's easy salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: shrimp and scallop pilaf
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter; stir in turmeric.
Add rice, onion and garlic.
Cook about 3 minutes until onion is translucent, stirring often.
Pour in broth; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add scallops, shrimp and peas.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes longer or until scallops are opaque, shrimp turn pink and peas are heated.
Taste and season.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients; stir in Rice Krispies.
Place small ball on floured, not greased, cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients except shrimp in blender, then add shrimp.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Goes great with Triscuit crackers!

title: cream cheese pineapple dip
directions: Blend or beat well, adding pineapple juice until of dip or spread consistency.
Excellent for cracker spread or chip dip.

title: southern fried rabbit
directions: Rabbit southern fried the same way as frying chicken is a good recipe.

title: easy 1-2-3 tuna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Remove frozen pie crust shell from its tin and set on wax paper.
Combine tuna, veggies and soup in mixing bowl.
Put mixture into pie tin.
Place pie crust over tuna mixture.
Split crust into several places.
Don't seal edge.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until crust is golden.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and pepper; drain.
Put all ingredients in large pan and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, green onions and olives.
Spread a thin layer of mixture on a tortilla.
Arrange four slices of ham over cheese.
Tightly roll up tortilla.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
To serve, unwrap tortillas and slice into 3/4-inch slices.
Makes about 64 appetillas.

title: baked fish
directions: If fillets are large, cut into serving size.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix juice, onion and butter mixture.
Place in greased pan.
Pour remaining butter mixture over fish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tasty thai shrimp and sesame noodles
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, mix shrimp with 1/3 of Newman's dressing.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
With a whisk, mix peanut butter, soy sauce, honey, ginger, crushed red peppers and remaining dressing; set aside.
After shrimp have marinated for 1 hour, prepare capellini as directed as label directs; drain.

title: bacon canapes
directions: Mix ingredients with Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Spread on fresh bread with crusts removed.
Cut into squares or triangles.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in butter. Alternate with sliced potatoes and carrots. Add soups and salt. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chinese cashew chicken
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, celery, chicken, water chestnuts, vegetables and half of noodles.
Mix good.
Use 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining noodles and cashews. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat the fruit with enough sugar to sweeten them.
While the fruit is heating, melt the margarine in baking dish.
Mix together with flour and sugar with enough water to make a thick batter that will pour.

title: souffle
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; pour in souffle dish and top with croutons.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, and cornstarch in saucepan, and cook until clear and thick.
Then take off stove.
Mix in jello with mixture, then pour over sliced strawberries in crust.
Chill and cover with cool whip.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice.
Add strawberries.
Put in baked pie shell or graham cracker shell. Makes 2 pies.

title: stuffed spinach mushrooms
directions: Stuff large mushrooms with spinach mixture.
Brush with butter.
Bake until brown.

title: ben's veal stew
directions: Combine flour and salt; dredge meat. Reserve excess flour. Brown meat in oil in Dutch oven; pour off drippings. Drain onions and reserve 1/2 c. liquid. Mix tomato sauce, sherry, parsley, thyme and garlic powder; add to meat and mix. Cover tightly and cook slowly 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Dissolve any remaining flour in onion liquid and use to thicken gravy. Stir in onions and mushrooms. Cook covered 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: light pumpkin pancakes
directions: In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
In small bowl, combine egg whites, milk, pumpkin and 2 Tbsp. oil; add to flour mixture; stir just until flour is moistened.

Heat griddle over medium heat until drop of water sizzles; brush lightly with oil. Pour batter by scant 1/4 c. onto hot griddle, making a few pancakes at a time; cook until tops are bubbly and edges look dry. With pancake turner; turn and cook until undersides are golden. Place on warm platter.
Repeat until all batter is used, brushing griddle with more oil if necessary.
Serve pancakes with syrup if desired.
Makes 16 pancakes.
Each pancake without syrup: about 96 calories, 2 g. fat, 0 mg. cholesterol, 150 mg. sodium.

title: alabama buttermilk biscuits
directions: Melt shortening and stir into warmed buttermilk. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to cooled buttermilk mixture. Combine dry ingredients with buttermilk and yeast mixture. At this point, batter can be rolled out and cut into biscuits or kept in mixing bowl (covered tightly) and placed in refrigerator for up to 5 days until ready to use. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into biscuits and dip in melted butter. Let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: marascarda
directions: Bring clam chowder to a rolling boil.
Clean and devein shrimp. Wash and debeard mussels.
Rinse clams, scallops and lobster tails.
Add crabs, lobster, shrimp and scallops.
Cook until done.
Then add the clams and mussels.
Boil until they peek open.
Set aside.
Cut the bread into circles.
Butter them and dip into Marascarda.

title: classic pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled margarine and anise or vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Blend into egg mixture until smooth, using a large spoon. Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon.
Bake in Pizzelle Baker.
Makes approximately 60.
For extra holiday fun, add several drops food coloring to dough.
Mangiare!

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken; debone it and place in bottom of large casserole dish. Put chopped onion on top of chicken, then sliced cheese over onion. Put broken Doritos over cheese.
Put soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes in blender; mix well. Pour over top of casserole. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Good with Mexican Salad.

title: green salad
directions: Whip first three ingredients. Separately mix 1 box of Dream Whip per instructions.
Fold into cream cheese. Then add marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix vegetables and salt together.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, water or corn juice and paprika.
Mix until sugar or Equal is dissolved.
Pour liquid mixture over vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Set aside.
Combine in a large saucepan sugar, Carnation milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil you cannot stir down.
Reduce heat and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into mixing bowl and quickly mix.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: pear honey
directions: Put pears through coarse food processor. Combine all ingredients and cook until thick and transparent.
Put in jars and process in water bath (boiling) for 5 minutes.

title: minted punch
directions: Boil 1 cup pineapple juice and sugar.
Crush fresh chopped mint; add to liquid and boil 5 minutes.
Add this mixture to remaining juice.
Add ginger ale or other lemon-lime drink at time of serving.
Garnish with fresh mint and lemon slices.
Serve over ice.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook onion.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in 3/4 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornish hens and rice
directions: Cover bottom of greased baking dish with rice (don't use seasoning package in rice mix).
Add small amount of poultry seasoning.
Mix soups and pour over rice.
Top with birds that have soaked overnight in white Port wine (first drain birds). Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: mexican stack dish
directions: Brown ground beef in a little water in frypan.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Put back onto stove and let simmer.
Pour chili in and let heat back up.
Put Doritos in dish.
Spoon chili meat mixture on top, then layer lettuce and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour Thousand Island dressing and taco sauce on top (to taste).
Cover with Dorito chips.

title: taco hot dish
directions: Brown the meat, drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning.
Spread crescent rolls in casserole dish.
Pour taco meat, then spread sour cream and sprinkle cheese and top off with crushed tortilla chips.
Use the temperature and length of time that is stated on crescent roll package.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 3/4 stick of oleo and saute onion in it.
Slice and cook squash until tender.
Drain squash and mash real good.
Add onion, 15 Ritz cracker crumbs, eggs, seasoning and cheese; mix well.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Melt the 1/4 stick of oleo, 15 more Ritz crackers, crumbled and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Bring soup to a boil.
Add cream cheese and beat until melted. Add gelatine (small package dissolved in 1/2 cup water); cool. Before it sets, add mayonnaise, chopped mixture and shrimp.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well the ingredients, then make out in balls, the size of walnuts. Put 1/2 cup kraut in bottom of pan. Place meatballs on kraut and cover them with the rest of kraut and juice.
Bake with lid on at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°. Bake for 45 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup ketchup with 1/4 cup water.
Pour over top and bake 20 minutes or longer until meatballs are done.

title: crock-pot baked bean salad
directions: Mix together beans and tomatoes.
Cut bacon in small pieces. Cut onions and peppers in rings.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in crock-pot on low all night.
Add any seasoning you like. Good and so easy to make.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix jello and water, then other ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Add dressing on top of salad.

title: pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, salt and sugar to a boil and then let cool. Add spices, sliced cucumbers and onions to cooled mixture.
Place all ingredients in large jar and store in refrigerator for minimum of two days.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, 1 cup sour cream, salt and pepper.
Quick fry 1 tortilla at a time in hot oil to soften.
Spoon a heaping tablespoonful of chicken mixture onto each.
Spread down center and roll.
Place, seam side down, in an oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spoon enchilada sauce over tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and enchiladas are hot.

title: oatmeal refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour scalded milk over shortening, sugar and salt until shortening melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 1 cup flour and eggs.
Add softened or proofed yeast; fold in oats.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough. Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until satiny, about 10 minutes.
Pound dough into a ball and place in greased ball. Brush with melted shortening.
Cover and let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine 4 cups bread crumbs, eggs, salt, pepper, shrimp, crab, mushrooms, pimento, onion salt and parsley.
Mix lightly; pour into large buttered baking dish.
Mix soup, cream and mayonnaise, blending well.
Pour over fish mixture.
Mix 1/2 cup bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves 10.

title: festive caramel bars
directions: Combine caramel candies and milk, in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until caramels are melted and wel blended.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place close together in a greased pan and bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix chocolate pudding, milk and Kahlua together.
Place 1 cake layer in bottom of trifle dish.
Top with 1/2 pudding mixture. Sprinkle crushed Skor bars on top.
Spread 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip on top.
Place other cake layer next and repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip as frosting.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Mix meat and Dale's sauce enough to coat meat.
Wash mushrooms and cut in half.
Wash and cut peppers in 1 inch pieces. Wash tomatoes.
Begin Layering Kabobs-- meat, pineapple, red pepper, mushroom, tomato, green pepper and repeat.
Place on grill.
Cook 4 minutes on each side turn and brush with pineapple juice.
Continue cooking 2 minutes on each side until meat is done.
This is great with rice.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Beat in flour, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Blend in butter, chocolate chips and chopped walnuts. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Arrange peas and carrots on top.
Put slices of eggs over this.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
After Jell-O is partly congealed, fold in the other ingredients.
Chill at least 5 hours.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Boil together sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter and set aside. Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening.
Then add milk and stir.
Roll out dough.
Wrap apples (peel and core apples) with dough.
Dot with butter.
Put in baking dish.
Pour on syrup.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: glazed apple cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda, blend shortening, sugar, salt, spices and egg.
Stir in 1/2 of flour mixture, then nuts, apples and raisins.
Blend in liquid and remaining flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: mini ham sandwiches
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients until butter is melted.
Mix well. Slice rolls in halves.
Put slice of ham and cheese inside. Arrange on cookie sheet in single layers.
Pour butter mixture over all and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Reserve 2 to 4 tablespoons of the fried bacon for topping. Mix the remaining ingredients in a microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle the reserved bacon on top.
Bake in the microwave on High for at least 20 minutes or until firm.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: In a bowl, mix pudding with 1/2 cup less milk than recipe calls for.
Beat until thick.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Fold in whipped topping. Chill.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/2 cup melted margarine in a bowl.
Stir in sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine corn flake crumbs and 1/2 cup melted margarine; sprinkle on top.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: fish dinner quickie
directions: Bring 1/4 cup water to a boil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and frozen lima beans.
After water returns to boiling point, simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Separate defrosted fish fillet and arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, lemon juice and thyme.
Stir tomato soup into hot lima beans, then pour this mixture over fish.
Cover and bake in hot 400°
oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eight vegetable soup with millet
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add hulled millet.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until millet is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove saucepan from heat and fluff millet with a fork and set aside.

title: no fail dumplings
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out thin and let stand 20 minutes. Cut in strips and cook until done.

title: chili cheese cornbread
directions: Mix Jiffy corn bread according to package directions.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs with cream.
Add dry ingredients and rhubarb; pour in pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Combine chicken, vegetables, soup and milk.
Mix in 3/4 cup of French fried onions.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle on the rest of the French fried onions.
Return to the oven for a few minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pasta with fresh basil and garlic
directions: Cook linguine to desired doneness as directed on package; drain.
Keep warm.

title: poppy seed lemon loaves
directions: Mix together cake mix, gelatin and poppy seeds. Beat in eggs, salad oil and water. Pour into 4 small, greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Wait 10 minutes before turning out. Freeze. Slice frozen. Make sandwiches with softened butter. Refrigerate or freeze. Serve cold.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Add egg, well beaten, with milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
When thick, add salt and vanilla.
Makes 1 (8-inch) pie.

title: lazy man's meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the cheese.
Place into a loaf dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in the oven at 400° for 55 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecued pork chops or pork steak
directions: Place some oil in frypan to brown pork chops slightly.
Add water to almost cover them; let them simmer for several minutes. Place sliced onions on top.
Cover all with the tomato, water and pickle juice.
Cook until done.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Stir in flour, bouillon and mustard.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves and mixture thickens slightly.
Remove from heat.
Break 10 slices of cheese into pieces.
Stir into mixture until melted. Stir in macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese slices (broken into bits).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: meaty spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Cook bacon and set aside.
Cook pork, sausage and pepperoni in bacon fat slowly until pork is done.
Add bacon, pork and pepperoni to tomato sauce.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours and add water as needed.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: cucumbers, onion and tomatoes
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Makes enough to cover one small cucumber, 2 medium onions and one or two tomatoes.

title: snickerdoodle salad
directions: Cut and cube Snickers and apples; add to Cool Whip.
Prepare just before serving.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cake mix and flour.
Mix well.
Let rise until double in size.
Divide into 2 or 3 batches. Roll on floured board.
Spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle generously with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll into a long roll and cut into rolls about 1-inch thick.
Let rise again until about double in size.
Bake in 375° oven about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix
and
put into buttered 2 quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and milk to 238° to 240°, the soft ball stage when tested in cold water.
Remove from the fire and add peanut butter and salt. Do not stir.
When cool, add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered tin and cut into squares.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Mix soup, water and flour until smooth.
Combine with other ingredients in crock-pot and cook all day.
Serve over egg noodles or with crunchy French bread.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onion.
Cook as directed on package and drain.
Combine vegetables with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add salt, baking powder and flour.
Fold in sour cream with a spoon.
In a separate bowl, mix brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased 9x13 pan or bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of brown sugar mixture over batter; repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour pie filling into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and spread evenly.
Add sugar, then cake mix.
Put margarine slices on top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: royal philadelphia cinnamon buns
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
To this cut in the shortening.
To this add milk and egg mixture.
Stir until makes a soft dough.
Roll out very thin.
Spread softened butter over dough.

Sprinkle with brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon. Begin at edge nearest you and roll up like you would a jelly roll. Cream 6 tablespoons butter and 6 tablespoons brown sugar and spread thickly on bottom and sides of baking pan or skillet.
With sharp knife cut the dough in 2 inch pieces and place in pan with cut side up.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cook at 425° for 25 minutes.
Remove at once, upside-down.

title: super easy pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease pan.
Bake at 325° in a Bundt pan or loaf pan, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch pans bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mystery pie
directions: Grease an aluminum pie pan.
Put in mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Place in refrigerator; cool.
Just before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature.
Combine cheeses and mix well.
Blend in pimentos, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, cayenne and salt.
Form into ball with hands. Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm.
Reshape into balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly and shape into a ball or log.
Roll in finely chopped nuts or minced parsley.

title: grandma pilkington's baked custard\
directions: Scald milk.
Butter 5 custard cups; place buttered cups into baking pan which has water in it.
Mix eggs and sugar, nutmeg, vanilla and salt.
Pour scalded milk into mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set so you can take a knife out clean.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all together and spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cut in small squares and serve.

title: perfect cookies
directions: Boil raisins for 5 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Stir in soda.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add cooled raisins with liquid.
Then add flour sifted with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Leave space between each cookie.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 425° oven.
Remove at once.

title: white clam sauce
directions: *Fresh chopped clams work even better.

title: bean salad
directions: Heat oil, vinegar and sugar to boiling point.
Pour over the rest of the ingredients.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix in bowl.
Add sugar, cherry juice and lemon juice to fruit.
Blend Cool Whip with mayonnaise and fold into fruit.
Put into a square cake pan and cover with foil.
Put in freezer.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.
Use as a salad or dessert.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and powder together.
Set aside.
Cream sugars, shortening and peanut butter.
Next, mix in vanilla and slightly beaten eggs.
Combine both bowls; mix thoroughly.
Shape well rounded teaspoonfuls of cookie dough into balls.
Press top of each in crisscross fashion with fork to flatten.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hurry up chicken salad
directions: Discard broth from chicken breast or freeze for dumplings later on.
Put meat in large pan and take a fork and start pulling the strands apart.
This is important!
Chicken breast is dry and will pick up flavor better if real fine.
After pulling breast, add onion and mayo and mix well.
Add pepper if you want.
Cover and let set for an hour in fridge or eat now; it gets better with time.
Serve with Club crackers, pickles and cheese or on celery sticks.
This is so easy and good.

title: creative play dough
directions: Cook all ingredients over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes, stirring vigorously until it forms a ball.
Remove dough from saucepan.
Let stand on counter for 5 minutes.
Knead for 30 seconds or until smooth and blended.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Melt 2 sticks butter.
Crush 60 Ritz crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix with melted butter.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook celery, bell pepper and onion in butter, then add soups, chicken broth, chili powder, Tabasco sauce and salt. Cook chicken and spaghetti. Mix all together and top with cheese.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, prepare pudding mix according to package directions. As pudding begins to thicken, add sour cream and 1 cup Cool Whip topping. Mix well. Line a small size roasting pan with vanilla wafers. Slice bananas and place one layer of bananas over top of wafers. Cover bananas and wafers with half of pudding mixture. Repeat layers of vanilla wafers and bananas and cover with remaining pudding mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip topping over top of pudding. Cover with plastic wrap or foil and refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: amaretto custard cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup Bundt cake pan. Beat all ingredients in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 1 minute.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl, 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in middle comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Good chilled.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain off grease.
Crumble up bread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Layer cooked sausage, then grated cheese on bread.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: enchanted broccoli forest
directions: To make trees - cut off stalks of broccoli and cut into spears. Combine rice and water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cover. Cook until done (20 - 30 min.).
Fluff with a fork.
Meanwhile - saute' butter, onion, garlic, salt, dill weed, pepper, mint, & cayenne pepper.
Add to cooked rice - mix well.
Beat together eggs, parsley, cheese - mix into rice mixture.
Spread into buttered 10 x 6-inch pan.
Steam broccoli until tender.
Rinse in cold water, drain.
Arrange broccoli upright in bed of rice mixture and drizzle trees with lemon butter.
Bake 30 min. at 325°.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Sift cake flour and baking powder.
Blend gradually into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.

title: bubbly berry bliss(diabetic recipe)
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine club soda and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Stir in strawberries.
Chill until set.
One serving equals 1/2 fruit (also low in sodium and cholesterol).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place Doritos and then chicken on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients except for cheese and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: hambuger hash
directions: Brown ground beef in a large frying pan. Make sure beef is finely crumbled. Drain well. Add 2-3 shakes ofworcestershire and mix well. Chop potatoes into small pieces and add to beef.
Mix well and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender. Add catsup to coat mixture.

title: waffles or pancakes(milk-free and egg-free)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat; more water may be added to acquire desired thickness. Bake in a hot waffle iron or on a hot griddle.

title: baked brie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cheese on sheet pan.
Put raisins, walnuts and apples on cheese.
Place in oven for 10 minutes.
Serve with bread or crackers when finished.

title: giant oreos
directions: Beat until creamy the butter and lard.
Gradually beat sugar into this.
Then add salt, cinnamon and melted cocoa.
Add well beaten egg.
Add soda dissolved in milk.
Stir in about 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with round cutter.
Bake in quick oven.
Use as little flour as possible for rolling.
Frost after cooled with buttercream frosting, putting two cookies together like a sandwich.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In 4-quart stock pot, saute beef, onion, Worcestershire sauce and butter.
Add tomato soup and stewed tomatoes.
Add water, carrots, green beans, okra, pinto beans, corn , bouillon cubes, cooking wine, chili powder and garlic powder.
Bring to boil. Turn down heat and cover; let simmer 2 to 4 hours.
Thirty minutes before serving, add macaroni.
Let simmer.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Serves 8.

title: cape cod clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in 3 or 4-quart pot until crisp.
Remove and drain bacon.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons grease.
Add onion and saute until translucent.
Add potatoes, water, clams, salt, pepper and shake in flour.
Stir.
Cover pot and simmer 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, crumble in bacon and heat, stirring occasionally until hot, without boiling.
Yields:
2 quarts.

title: good-n-easy salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O and sugar.
Dissolve.
Add mayonnaise and milk.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: grandma's sausage and potato stew
directions: Make a roux.
Add onion and bell pepper; saute.
Add water, potatoes and sausage; season to taste.
Cook until potatoes are done (approximately 25 minutes).

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 3 minutes.
Freeze in gallon container.
Remove from freezer for 1 hour before serving.
Pour ginger ale or 7-Up over frozen mix.

title: fudge chocolate layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
In a saucepan, melt butter and chocolate, stirring over low heat.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Bake your potatoes.
Scoop out the potato out of the skin. Mash the potato; add shredded cheese, chives, minced onions, bacon bits, butter, garlic and whatever you like.
Stuff it back in the skin and bake again.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and honey in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.
Take out; add soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir well (will change color and look like its curdling).
Pour over popcorn. Make sure roaster is sprayed with Pam.
Coat evenly.
Bake at 250° for
1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine catsup, onion, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed, 1/4 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or desired consistency.

title: excellent fudgy brownies(1957 betty crocker's cookbook for boys and girls)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate and shortening together.
Remove from heat. Beat in 1 cup sugar and 2 eggs.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach following directions, then drain well.
Add to other ingredients.
Chill.
Round pumpernickel may be hollowed out and dip put in the middle or bread can be cubed and dip put into a dish.

title: sausage or ham and cheese brunch tarts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease 12 cup muffin tin.
Cook and stir sausage until brown.
(If using cubed ham, doesn't need to be cooked second time.)
Mix baking biscuit mix and margarine.
Add boiling water.
Stir vigorously until soft dough forms.
Press 1 level tablespoon of dough on bottom of each muffin cup.
Press on bottom and up side of each cup.
Divide sausage/ham evenly among cups.
Beat half and half and egg.
Stir in onions and salt.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon into each cup.
Sprinkle cheese over tops.
Bake until edges are golden brown and center is set, about 25 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Season crawfish and set aside.
Melt margarine in Dutch oven. Add flour and stir until blended.
Add chopped onions, bell pepper and celery; cook on low heat until tender or about 20 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Add crawfish tails and fat; cover.
Add 2 cups of water.
Season to taste with let cook 30 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add green onion tops and parsley.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve over warm rice.

title: lipton pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin 2-inch strips.
In a large skillet, heat shortening and brown meat.
Stir in onion soup and 2 cups water. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in peppers and simmer for 10 more minutes.
Blend in cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Cook, while stirring, until thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in celery and onion.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mash shrimp with a fork and add to mixture.
Refrigerate several hours before serving. May be served with Fritos, Doritos or crackers.
May be prepared 2 days in advance and allowed to marinate.
Makes 1 quart.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients for 2 hours and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 1 hour slowly after it comes to a boil.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: In a 9 X 13-inch baking dish, place melted butter.
In a bowl, mix flour, baking powder, sugar, milk, egg, and vanilla. Pour over butter.
Do not mix.
Top with fruit and juice.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes, or until brown.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Cook egg noodles 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain ground beef and onions.
Put in large sized casserole dish.
Mix egg noodles and both cans of soup.
Stir into ground beef and onions until well mixed.
Cover top with whole potato chips.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bacon and water chestnuts
directions: Mix water chestnuts, soy sauce and maple syrup together and let stand 4 hours.
Wrap water chestnut with bacon and sauce with a toothpick.
Sprinkle with granulated brown sugar and cook at 350° until bacon is cooked.

title: gramma's banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and beat with eggs until light. Add butter. Sift together flour, sugar, salt and soda. Mix with banana mixture. Add nuts and flavoring. Stir well and put in well greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Use same recipe for date bread, substituting 2 cups chopped dates for bananas. Do not overbake.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix vegetables and set aside.
Boil vinegar and sugar together about 1 minute.
Make sure sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
When cool, pour over vegetables.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator. Best when allowed to sit overnight.
Keeps well.
Good side dish with barbecue.

title: ripe tomato relish *
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers and onions; add remaining ingredients. Cook slowly for approximately 1 1/2 or 2 hours or until thick. Seal in hot jars.
Makes about 2 1/2 pints.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Mix jello and marshmallows; add water, pineapple and bananas. Chill until firm.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix gelatin and hot water.
Add cheese and mix until well blended.
Add marshmallows, drained pineapple and 7-Up.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and place in refrigerator.
I usually top the salad with pecans.

title: bacon, lettuce and tomato pizzas
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and tear into bite size pieces and set aside.
In a large bowl, toss lettuce, tomatoes and onion with mayonnaise.
Add bacon and toss a bit more.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add biscuit mix and mix well, then knead about 1 minute on a board dusted with biscuit mix (or until smooth).
Shape into rolls and put on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise in a warm place about 1 hour.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool before adding filling.

title: garlic and lemon artichokes
directions: Combine 6 tablespoons margarine with garlic and set aside. Cut stems off artichokes and trim leaves.
Place lemon slices between leaves and put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour margarine
mixture over artichokes.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High 12 to 14 minutes.
Combine 2 tablespoons margarine with remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over artichokes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer half of the corn flakes, all of the cabbage and water chestnuts.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and soup together and pour over the cabbage.
Top with Cheddar cheese, margarine and the rest of the corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill and serve.
Great for veggies!

title: spice bars
directions: In a small pan, simmer water, raisins and shortening for 20 minutes with lid on; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spread on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together and press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake until light brown at 350°.
Let cool.

title: bean soup
directions: Put 1 quart water, beans, ham hock and celery in large kettle. Brown bacon with onion and add to beans.
Simmer about 3 hours. Add diced potatoes and simmer 1 hour longer with 1 cup water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: bourbon balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup powdered sugar and remaining ingredients.
Sift remaining cup of powdered sugar onto a sheet of wax paper.
Using your hands, shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Roll each ball in sugar.
For best storing, wrap each ball in a small square of plastic or foil.

title: apple roll
directions: Combine ingredients to form dough.
Roll dough out on floured board.
Spread with melted butter (1 1/4 cups), 2 cups grated apples, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Roll up like jelly roll and slice into 1 or 2-inch pieces.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Mix all together, then pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: three layer pie
directions: Mix vanilla and chocolate pudding mixes and milk until mixture becomes pudding.
Spread on second layer.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Saute onions, salt and pepper. Then add ground beef until brown.
Add tomato sauce, cheese and rice.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove the top and seeds from peppers.
Boil peppers in salted water for 5 minutes.
Take out and stuff.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: noodle pie
directions: Take fresh sausage out of skin and brown.
Mix all ingredients together and put in pan.
(Don't cover pan.) Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Mix ingredients; heat thoroughly on top of stove.
Can use mixture as a topping for baked potatoes, etc.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Cut bread loaf or rolls in half, lengthwise.
Spread with butter.
Combine beef, Parmesan cheese, seasonings, onion, tomato paste and olives.
Spread mixture on cut slices of bread loaf or rolls.
Place unwrapped loaves or servings, meat side up, on cookie sheet.
Top with tomato slices.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with cheese slices in between each tomato slice.
Return to oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: berkly hot spiced cider
directions: Tie cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg in a small piece of cheesecloth.
Combine with cider and sugar in large saucepan; simmer 15 minutes and remove spice bag.
Stir in orange and lemon juices.
Heat until bubbling.
Pour into heated punch bowl; add small oranges studded with whole cloves for garnish.
Add apple brandy if wanted.

title: fruit salad fat-free
directions: Mix all together.
Great to serve over fat-free vanilla yogurt to make a sundae.
Also good as a fruit salad.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Cook all ingredients in a large pan until it cooks down. Serve.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Into a very large bowl, put buttermilk, sugar and baking soda; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until it turns brownish in color and reaches soft ball stage. Stir constantly.
Test by dropping a small amount into cool water to see if it forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, margarine and pecans; beat until it becomes glossy and starts to crystallize.
Quickly spoon out onto wax paper into little patties.
Let cool.
If candy starts to turn sugary and hardens too fast, return to heat for a few minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix
the
first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Stir and put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: kitchen pepper
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Keep in a tightly corked bottle, or use a bottle with a screw top that has holes to shake pepper out.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Mix well and spread over chicken mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Bake uncovered 10 to 15 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: light bread rolls
directions: Combine together and add 5 to 6 cups flour.
Put in refrigerator about 50 minutes before you bake.
Make into rolls. Let rise until double and then bake at 350° until done.

title: endive with ham and cheese(dutch)
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add flour and mix until smooth.
Add salt and pepper; mix.
Slowly add milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 of cheese.
Mix until smooth.
Wash endive and remove a small conical piece with a sharp knife from stalk end of endive.
(Discard this conical piece; it will make vegetable less bitter.)
Splash endive with lemon juice and steam them for 12 to 15 minutes.
(They'll be tender.) Roll endive in paper towels to remove excess moisture. Wrap each endive in ham.
Place in a greased casserole dish and pour cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining grated cheese and dot with butter.
Broil until the cheese is golden.
(Dish can be made in advance and baked at 350° for 30 minutes, then broiled briefly.)
Serves 6.

title: aunt jan's twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes (oil skins) at 400° for 55 minutes.
Cut potatoes lengthwise in half.
Hollow out potatoes in large bowl and mash thoroughly.
In large skillet, heat 3 to 4 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add onions and saute.
Add crumbled bacon, potatoes, sour cream, 1/2 of the cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Add mixture to skins, place pats of butter on top and sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Place in skins in baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Bake uncovered at 350° for 12 to 20 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes(baked)
directions: Instead of using milk to mash potatoes, use French onion dip with sour cream.

title: new england corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon; remove from pan.
Saute onion in part of bacon fat.
Add potatoes and chicken stock.
Season with celery seed and dill seed.
When tender, add corn, milk and half and half.
Heat to boiling; season.
Serve with diced bacon on top.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients to juice, egg, cranberries and pecans. Pour into bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Bread freezes well.

title: foil-baked turkey
directions: Sprinkle underside of turkey lightly with salt.
Cream butter, cheese, flour, herbs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper together. Spread over skin of turkey.
Place on sheet of heavy foil and bring edges together up over meat and fold over twice.
Fold ends twice to seal.
Place packet in a shallow baking pan and roast in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 50 minutes.
Open foil carefully and pour off juices.
Slice meat and serve with juices.

title: chicken salad summer delight(party of 35 to 40 people)
directions: Boil chicken about 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Shred chicken or dice (boneless).
Dice celery stalk; add to cold chicken.
Add drained pineapple and mayonnaise.
Add salt according to taste. Great for sandwiches or filling tomatoes or even stuff bell peppers.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except oats and peanut butter.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and peanut butter.
If thin, add more oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk and boil 7 minutes.
Stir often or constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add other items.
Mix until smooth.
Pour in well buttered pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix everything together EXCEPT one stick melted butter.
Put into buttered casserole dish (9 x 13), then pour over the 2nd stick of butter.
May also save a little cheese to sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350 for about 45 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese well.
Drain shrimp and mash with fork. Add finely chopped onion.
Mix Miracle Whip or mayonnaise with cream cheese mixture.
Add more or less to desired consistency. Chill.

title: chilighetti
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onions, spaghetti and beans. Mix together remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour juice mixture over ground beef mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles for 10 to 15 minutes, until tender (do not overcook).
Mix soup and tuna in a small pot; cook for 7 minutes. Mix soup and tuna and noodles in large pot.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Break bread into small pieces; spread on top of casserole.
Cook in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Bring all ingredients to full boil except carrots and boil about 3 minutes.
Add carrots and cook 3 to 5 minutes over medium heat.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in oil in skillet.
Place in slow cooker.
Add soy sauce, bouillon cube, garlic, onion, bell pepper and 1 cup water. Cook for 5 to 6 hours or until tender.
Stir in mixture of cornstarch and 1/4 cup water until thickened.
Serve over hot brown rice.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly; continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring in chocolate pieces until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.

title: strawberries & cream bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Add all remaining ingredients & stir gently.
DO NOT USE MIXER!
Pour into greased Bundt pan, or 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, and then remove onto cooling rack.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix next three ingredients and add to melted butter.
Add fruit and bake at 375° about 40 minutes until brown.

title: microwave rice casserole
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Add rice.
Add mushrooms.
Stir and cover.
Microwave for 12 minutes on High.
Stir and cook an additional 3 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in square pan and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Stir together cake mix, oil & eggs using spoon.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Insert wooden stick in edge of dough until tip is in center.
Bake 8-10 minutes or until puffed and almost no indentation remains where touched.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool completely, about 30 minutes.
Frost and decorate as desired.

title: spanish lima beans
directions: Fry onion and pepper slowly in butter until golden. Add tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes. Add seasonings and drained beans. Alternate layers of bean mixture and cheese in a greased 1-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Heat mixture until sugar dissolves.
Watch carefully as it tends to boil over. Spread wings in two 9 x 13 inch pans. Pour about 1 c. of marinade over the wings. (Tip:
Line pans with aluminum foil for easy clean-up.
Marinade tends to get sticky when baked on.) Marinate for 24 hours or more for best results.

title: baked scallops
directions: Lay spinach leaves in a greased
inch pan and spread scallops over them. Combine butter, crumbs and shallots and crumble over scallops. Bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes.

title: one punch recipe with tea
directions: Combine.
Makes a large amount for big parties.

title: asian salad
directions: Place chopped cabbage, onions and crushed noodles in a bowl. Saute sesame seed and almonds in butter.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to become dressing. Toss all ingredients together. Pour dressing over. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: daddy's favorite raisin pie
directions: Simmer together raisins, water, vinegar, sugar and flour. Add nuts.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 360° for 25 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Put milk in double boiler.
Mix sugar and flour; add to milk. Add butter and vanilla.
Cook in double boiler until thick; cool. To the baked pie crust, add a layer of thinly sliced bananas, a layer of the sauce, another layer of bananas and remainder of sauce.
Cover with meringue; bake until brown.

title: cream cheese and olive spread
directions: Mix well and serve at room temperature.
If you refrigerate, remove at least one hour before serving.
If it is too cold, it crumbles and will not spread.

title: vegetable meatballs
directions: Mix meat, cheese, vegetables, rice and seasonings.
Form meat into balls, about 1/2 cup each.
Mix soup, ketchup and water. Pour sauce into baking dish and arrange meatballs.
Baste meatballs with sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 24 hour cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage and green pepper.
Pour sugar over cabbage mixture.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate (overnight is best).
Will keep indefinitely in a covered container.

title: 5 fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough on pizza pan.
Bake as directed.
Cool. Blend cream cheese and sugar; put on top of cookie.
Slice banana into pineapple juice to prevent banana from turning.
Arrange fruit on cookie, starting at center and going all over cookie.

title: cheesy rice broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to a boil.
Stir in Velveeta.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: french toast
directions: Preheat a skillet to 325°.
In a large bowl, mix eggs and beat with a fork until mixed well.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Beat with fork some more.
Dip bread in mixture, completely covering both sides.

title: green chili chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and add cheese on top before baking.
You can add water if mixture is too thick.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cashew chicken stir-fry
directions: In a skillet, heat 3 tablespoons of broth. Meanwhile, combine the cornstarch, soy sauce, ginger and remaining broth until smooth. Set aside. Add chicken to the skillet. Stir-fry over medium heat until no longer pink, about 3 to 5 minutes. Remove with a slotted spoon and keep warm. Add garlic, carrots and celery to skillet. Stir-fry for 3 minutes. Add broccoli and peas. Stir-fry for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender. Stir broth mixture. Add to the skillet with the chicken. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in cashews. Serve over rice, if desired. Yield: 4 servings.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix butter and flour.
Add cider and raisins, a little at a time.
Cook all ingredients together on low heat until thickened. Recipe of Jane Irvin.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells until tender.
Drain and cool on wax paper. Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Combine meat, eggs, Stove Top (croutons), Mozzarella cheese and spices.
Mix well.
Spread about an inch layer of spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Fill each shell with meat mixture and place open side down in dish.
Cover with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: After mixing all ingredients, stir every 30 minutes for 2 hours.
Store in sealed container.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and baking soda in large bowl.
Stir in buttermilk, molasses, melted shortening and raisins until well mixed.
Spoon batter into 4 well-greased 1 pound vegetable or fruit cans.
Cover with aluminum foil and tie with string.
Place cans on a rack in large kettle.
Pour boiling water to come halfway up sides of cans.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Pour in more boiling water if necessary, to keep cans in boiling water to the halfway point.
Remove from kettle and remove foil.
Cool in cans for 10 minutes on a rack.
Invert loaves onto rack.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and the jello in boiling water. Make the frozen lemonade by the directions on the can. Add all the ingredients, except the ginger ale. this will make 3 plastic gallon jugs almost full, ready to freeze. Add 1 bottle of ginger ale to 1 jug of punch when ready to serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix everything together except oleo and 1/2 of cracker crumbs. Put in baking dish and put rest of cracker crumbs on top.
Pour melted oleo on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350°.

title: aunt jenny's jello salad
directions: Cook jello according to package.
Chill until partially set. Add pineapple, cheese and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar together and place in buttered casserole.
Melt butter. Mix butter, oatmeal and nuts together. Sprinkle on top of mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great at Thanksgiving!! Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: white cookies
directions: Let stand in cool place overnight. Roll in morning and bake.

title: chicken broccoli salad
directions: Combine bulgur and 2/3 cup boiling water in a large bowl; let stand 30 to 45 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Set aside. Combine bouillon granules, garlic and remaining 2 cups boiling water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high heat; add chicken.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and let cool.
Discard broth.
Bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine with reserved bulgur.
Steam broccoli 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add to chicken mixture.
Add green onions, lime juice, pepper, red pepper flakes and ginger root to chicken mixture, tossing well.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bacon over butter.
Place chicken in dish.

title: lemon filling
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in double boiler.
Cook until ingredients coat spoon and liquid thickens.
Add beaten egg with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter or margarine and lemon rind.
Cool.
Spread on two layer cake.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix margarine, graham cracker crumbs, pecans, coconut, powdered sugar, vanilla and peanut butter. Form balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Stick toothpick in ball and dip in chocolate. Let cool.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water.
Boil to hard boil.
Add slowly to beaten egg whites.
Beat until holds peak and drop.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: fresh tomato and basil sauce
directions: Melt butter in a medium noncorrosive skillet.
Add garlic and tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes, or until tomatoes are softened. Add vermouth and cook on high heat until slightly thickened, about 4 minutes.
Add broth and continue to cook on high heat for 2 minutes longer, or until sauce thickens slightly.
Stir in pepper, salt and basil.
Taste for seasoning.
Toss with hot pasta in a serving bowl and garnish with basil.
Pass grated Parmesan cheese for each person to sprinkle to taste.
Serves 4.
tags: lots of freshly ground black pepper

title: potato chip casserole
directions: Brown your ground beef and sausage together, then drain.
Melt Velveeta in a slow cooker; add salsa and meat mixture.
Dip into bowls and eat with your choice of chips (Frito scoops or tortilla chips).

title: two minute fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and boil 2 minutes. Set pan in cold water and beat until thick.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: mexican goulash
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef.

title: chicken spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover and save broth.
Bone chicken; cut into small pieces.
In large, heavy saucepan, saute onions, garlic and celery in hot drippings.
Add parsley as mixture cooks. Add tomato sauce, soup, paste and seasonings.

title: ethel's pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour. Pour in tube pan that has been buttered and floured on bottom. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: low-fat marinated chicken
directions: Pour dressing and soy sauce in skillet.
Heat to boiling. Blend with whisk.
Reduce heat to medium.
Place chicken breasts in skillet and dump mushrooms on top, if desired.
Cover skillet and cook 4 to 6 minutes.
Turn breasts and cook additional 4 to 6 minutes until juice runs clear when poked with fork.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Fold in rhubarb.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Place potatoes, carrots, celery and onions in a large pan; cover with water and cook until tender.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and soup.
Add milk, salt, pepper and bacon.
Add to vegetables and heat through.

title: lucky's quick and easy beef steak
directions: Pound the Parmesan cheese into the steaks. Roll steaks lightly in the flour and season with the salt and pepper.
Saute the steaks slowly in hot fat.

title: open face hamburgers
directions: Put hamburger in bowl.
Put all ingredients into meat, except crackers.
Roll crackers into small pieces and mix all together like a meat loaf.
Put slices of bread on cookie sheet; spread meat on each slice of bread.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° or 375° until cheese is melted, meat is done and bread is toasted.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well and pour into two unbaked pie shells.	Bake at 350° for about
minutes
or until firm in center.
Makes 2 pies.

title: no fail chocolate icing
directions: Boil on 2 (next to highest) until can't stir down for 1 minute.
Then beat
with
mixer
for
minutes
or
until it thickens and loses its gloss.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix first seven ingredients until well blended, either by hand or in a blender.
Stir in cheese gently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups. Keeps well for 2 weeks if refrigerated.

title: mashed carrots
directions: Place carrots in a microsafe baking dish with 4 tablespoons water.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High power for 10 minutes or until tender.
In a food processor or blender, puree carrots.
Add butter, brown sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg to carrots.
Mix until very smooth.
Add parsley, thyme or marjoram. Pour carrot puree into a microsafe baking dish.
Microwave on High power for 6 to 8 minutes or until hot.
Serve with beef or chicken dishes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk and add Cool Whip.
Make 3 layers of graham crackers and 2 layers of pudding.
Cover with pudding.
Topping contains the rest of the ingredients not yet used.
Melt them together and add the powdered sugar last.

title: green pea salad
directions: Gently mix all ingredients.
Add mayonnaise to your liking. Chill several hours and serve on lettuce.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Put in a casserole dish.
Add the cream of mushroom soup.
Use the empty soup can to measure rice.
Mix 1 can of rice and water; add to hamburger.
Add seasoned salt to taste. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: six layer bars
directions: Melt butter; place in a small casserole dish.
Layer other ingredients in given order.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: pear butter
directions: Cook pear sauce and sugar 3 to 4 hours.
Add vanilla, vinegar and salt.
Stir well.

title: peach butter
directions: Peel, pit and chop peaches.
Cook in small amount of water until soft.
Press through sieve or food mill, or puree in blender.
Measure 2 quarts of pulp.

title: icing supreme
directions: Mix instant pudding and cold milk.
Mix in whipped topping. Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate.
Sugar-free pudding may be used.

title: lemon cream cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar and cream well.
Add beaten egg whites and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately. Begin and end with flour.
Bake in four 8-inch pans for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Drizzle over crackers.
Sprinkle nuts and marshmallows over crackers.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over mixture in pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon 'n crackers
directions: Wrap Waverly Wafers with thin strips of bacon.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours or until bacon is crisp.
These are so simple, but so delicious!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter. Add to Stove Top dressing. Mix well. Place zucchini, onion and carrots in saucepan. Add the chicken soup and sour cream; bring to a boil.

title: randy's do-it-yourself breakfast
directions: Split sausage down the middle. Microwave sausage 1 minute. Sprinkle sausage with cheese and broken up toast.
Microwave another 30 seconds.
(Substitute hot dog, if desired).

title: keebler fudge striped cookie salad
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix it all together and add 3/4 of the cookies.
When all mixed, sprinkle remaining cookies on top. Makes a large bowl full.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Add tomatoes and soups.
Spread Cheddar cheese.
Crush Doritos.
Add enough broth so that the mixture is not thick or dry.
Stir all ingredients together and bake until cheese melts.

title: potato cakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add onions, flour and egg.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on hot griddle.
Serve with boiled beef.

title: raspberry almond crepes
directions: Mix together well.
Use 1/4 cup for each crepe.
Fry in nonstick frying pan until brown.
Makes 12.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together 3 times.
Mix with next 6 ingredients.
Bake in an angel food pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pepper poppers
directions: Combine cheeses, bacon, and seasonings; mix well. Spoon about 2 tbsp. into each pepper half. Roll in breadcrumbs. Place on greased baking pan. Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Stir together with remaining ingredients.
Drop by small spoonfuls into hot oil. Turn once.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, boiling water and 7-Up. Add rest of ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: moo punch
directions: Add fruit juice to milk.
Blend in ice cream.

title: kit carson soup
directions: First make a roux (the cooking of flour and grease in equal portion, cooked in a large pot). Start with enough grease to cover the bottom of pot and add flour allowing the mass to thicken until it darkens to the color of peanut butter. Add ingredients.

Allow ingredients to simmer for 25 minutes. Add cooked fish and place lid on pot and simmer for another 30 minutes, being sure to stir carefully from side to side in pot every once and awhile to keep fish from sticking or burning to bottom of pot and replace lid.

title: meatballs in sour cream sauce
directions: In large bowl, combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, Parmesan cheese, milk, onion powder, garlic salt and pepper.
Form into 20 meatballs, using a rounded tablespoonful for each.
In large skillet, brown meatballs in oil; drain excess fat.
Sprinkle meatballs with paprika.
Add onion.
Cover; cook over low heat 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian banana cake(the cake that sara baked.)
directions: Set cream cheese aside to soften.
Mix cake as directed on package using milk instead of water.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° until done.
Remove from oven and punch pencil-size holes in the top (I use the end of a spatula).
Mix sugar and pineapple (with juice) and bring to a boil.
Then slowly pour over the cake.
Let set a few minutes.
Mix pudding as directed on the box.
Mix cream cheese with pudding using a mixer.
Spread over cake and cool in refrigerator (I let it set overnight).

title: layer dinner
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven.
When no longer pink, add in layers the sliced onion, potatoes and carrots.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Add parsley on top.
Cover tightly; turn heat low.
Cook for 45 minutes or until vegetables are done.

title: sissy spacek's walnut fudge cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
In small saucepan, melt oleo and chocolate; cool.

title: dieter's soup
directions: Cook until tender. Notice these are all white veggies. Others can be added though. Also mushrooms. This makes a lot and keeps well.

title: grandma's fudge
directions: Grease pot the fudge is cooked in to avoid crystallization. Boil the sugar, cocoa, salt, corn syrup and milk until forms a medium ball (small amount dropped into cold water).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add "good lump" of butter.
Add the chopped nuts, if desired.
Beat until almost thick enough.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: fried turkey fingers
directions: Marinate breast several hours in milk.
Cut breast into fingers; salt and pepper to taste.
Roll or shake fingers in flour.
Heat oil in pan; fry until brown.
Allow 1/4 to 1/3 pound per person.

title: rum cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar a little at a time.

Add 1/3 each of milk, flour and egg whites, in the order named, beating after each addition and beating well and long after the last addition. Keep out 2 tablespoons of flour, into which mix the baking powder. Add this when all beating is over.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: In large saucepan, over high heat, bring rice and broth to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and most of liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 20 minutes until all liquid is absorbed.

title: linguini and white clam sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add oil, garlic, onion and clams.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add remainder of spices.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add clam juice.
Serve over linguini.

title: pork and rice bake
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in skillet.
Place in baking pan and cover with rice.
Pour soup and milk mixture over the chops and rice.
Be careful to cover all rice with liquid. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chili mac(a pluma bennett favorite)
directions: Melt fat in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and beef.
Cook until brown.
About 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans, salt, chili powder and elbow macaroni.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato curry
directions: Fry chopped onion until light brown and add ginger paste, garlic paste, red chili powder and turmeric and fry for a few minutes.
Add one cup of water and salt and stir for a minute until onion becomes tender.
Add chopped tomatoes and cook until a thin gravy is formed.
Add potatoes (peeled and cut into big pieces) and fry for 10 minutes.
Add coriander powder.
Add 3 cups more water and cook on a low fire until tender.
Remove from the fire and sprinkle chopped coriander leaves and serve hot along with puri. Serves 8.

title: sesame noodles
directions: Bring large pot of salted water to boil. Add noodles and cook until al dente.
Drain.

title: "bigos" - polish hunters stew
directions: Brown beef in butter and remove from pan.
Add diced onion and diced apple.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Return beef to pan and add 1 cup beef broth, salt, pepper and allspice.
Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring 3 c. sugar, cream, butter, and baking soda to boil in a heavy sauce-pan.
Remove from heat, and keep warm.
Sprinkle remaining 3/4 c. sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over med. heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and syrup is light golden brown.
(Sugar will clump before melting.)
Gradually pour into whipping cream mixture.
(Mixture will bubble.)
Stir until smooth. Cook over med. heat, stirring often, 10-12 min. or until a candy thermometer registers 240 degrees (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Beat at high speed with an electric mixer until spreading consistency (8-10 min.)
Yield:
3 c. Great on layer cake.

title: fresh creamed corn
directions: Cut and scrape the corn off cobs.
Using large frypan or electric skillet, fry streak of lean until crisp.
Remove from pan. Add corn, salt and pepper to same pan.
Cook on medium heat for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue cooking on low heat until done.
Continue to stir every few minutes.
Cooking time is approximately 30 minutes.

title: string bean salad
directions: Cook beans in boiling salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Combine oil, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix with beans.
Lightly cover and chill.
Serve heaped on lettuce leaf and sprinkle with egg and cheese.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in a blender until smooth.
Chill and serve with vegetables, crackers and bread.

title: old fisherman's baked lima beans
directions: Rinse lima beans.
Add to boiling water and boil for about 2 minutes. Remove from stove. Cover pot and let it stand for about 1 hour.

title: pasta with italian sausage sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain; cover to keep hot.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Crumble the sausage and cook 5 minutes.
Stir until browned.
Add zucchini and onion; cover and cook until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Add sauce; heat through.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs until smooth; add dry ingredients.
Fold in old-fashioned Quaker oats last with a spoon. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet;
pat down and shape with wet fingers.
Bake at 325° approximately 12 minutes or until cooked or brown on edges.
Leave on pan approximately 1 minute before removing to wire rack.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together and add 12 ounce chocolate chips.
Bake in greased Bundt pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool 15 minutes before turning out onto cake dish.

title: sopaipillas (mexican fried bread)
directions: Sift
flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into a large bowl. Cut
in
shortening
until
mixture resembles cornmeal. Stir in milk until mixture forms a firm dough.
Knead dough on a
lightly floured surface just until smooth.
Cover; let rest 20
minutes. Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness; cut into squares or diamonds. Heat oil in a deep saucepan or deep fat fryer to 375°
on
deep fat frying thermometer.
Fry Sopaipillas, a few at
a
time, turning
often
so
they fry evenly until golden brown.
Remove from oil with a slotted spoon to paper toweling to
drain.
Serve hot
with
butter with a meal, or sprinkled with
cinnamon-sugar or
powdered sugar, or with a pitcher of warm honey, as a dessert.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of water just until tender. Drain and put in casserole dish.
Layer with cream of mushroom or chicken soup, mayonnaise, onion and cheese.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave fried chicken
directions: In paper bag, mix flour, salt and pepper with mustard; shake well.
Brush the chicken pieces with lemon juice.
Place a few pieces of chicken at a time in bag; shake until coated.
Remove; shake off excess flour from chicken.
Preheat 9-inch browning dish on High for 4 1/2 minutes.
Add oil and butter; arrange chicken (skin down) without crowding.
Cover loosely with waxed paper. Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Turn chicken; sprinkle with paprika. Cook on High 3 minutes.
Let stand, covered, with foil about 5 minutes before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes at medium speed. Batter will be thick.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini. Blend well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done when tested with a toothpick.
Cool in pans on wire rack.

title: slush
directions: Boil sugar and	2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Add jello, juice and remaining
water.
If
you
use lemon jello, use 1/2 ounce almond
flavoring.	Put
into
container
and
put	into freezer. Freeze until contents are slushy.

title: punch bowl cake
