directions: In a punch bowl, put pieces of angel food cake. Mix pudding as directed on package; spread half on cake, slice 3 bananas, pineapple, 1 can pie filling. Repeat, starting with cake, pudding, bananas, pineapple and pie filling. I put Cool Whip in between the layers. Put nuts on top.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream and flour alternately.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: one-step chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave-safe 2-quart casserole. Put microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir to break up meat and microwave additional 20 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.
One cup equals 4 ounces protein, 1 starch, 1/2 cup cooked vegetable.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water about 12 minutes.
Drain, rinse and cover with cold water.
Heat vegetable oil in saucepan. Add onions, carrots and garlic.
Saute until carrots are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and spices.
Bring to a simmer.
Beat eggs and blend in cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and vegetables.
Spread a thin layer of sauce over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with layer of noodles.
Cover with half of sauce.
Repeat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove foil.
Arrange olive slices over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, about 15 minutes, or until center is bubbly.
Let cook about 10 minutes to set layers.
Cut 2 x 3 into 4 1/2 x 4-inch pieces.
Yield:
6 servings.
Approximate calories: 326.

title: surprise greens
directions: Break into pieces to eat it right.
Cook it.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add other ingredients except crumbs. Put in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Bring 5 quarts of water and 1/4 cup Old Bay seasoning to a rolling boil in a large covered stockpot.
Add potatoes; return to a boil, and cook uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn, and return to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add shrimp to stockpot; cook 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Drain.
Serve with Old Bay seasoning and cocktail sauce. Makes 12 servings.

title: hot fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Stir in the cream and cook over low heat.
Add butter.
Continue to cook until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cup of cold water.
Remove from heat and place boiler in cool water.
Beat until desired consistency. Makes 1 cup.
Store in refrigerator.

title: nannie's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add eggs and mix well. Stir in flour and salt.
Dough will be wet, using just enough flour to roll out dough.
Roll to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: ambrosia dessert bowl
directions: Place marshmallows and 1/4 cup cream in the top of a double boiler; heat over boiling water until the marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool completely.
Meanwhile, whip the remaining cream until thick.
Add sugar.
Fold into marshmallow mixture.
Fold in extracts, pineapple and coconut.
Place half of the pound cake cubes in the bottom of a 2 1/2 to 3-quart clear glass bowl.
Top with half of the orange sections.
Top with half of the cream mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with almonds. Chill until serving time.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: chewy coconut cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, cream the butter and add sugars gradually, beating thoroughly. Add the egg.
Stir in the flour mixture until well blended.
Add the coconut and vanilla; mix well. Drop from teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet, about 3-inches apart. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring milk, butter, cocoa, sugar and salt to a rapid boil 2 minutes.
Mix well with peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: garden vegetable gratin
directions: Put vegetables in 2-quart microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add milk, white sauce mix, cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Microwave, covered, on High for 8 minutes.
Stir once and sprinkle remaining onions.
Microwave, uncovered, 1 minute. Serves 6.

title: onion puffs
directions: Spread on small bread rounds that have been pre-toasted on 1 side. Broil until golden brown & puffy. Makes about 20.

title: waffles
directions: Measure dry ingredients into mixing bowl and blend.
Combine egg yolks and milk.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in cooking oil and carefully fold in egg whites.
Do not overmix.
Pour approximately 2/3 cup batter into preheated griddle and close. Bake.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl; mix well.
Add 1/4 cup milk, oil, egg yolk and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl.
Add 1/4 cup milk and beat for 1 minute.
Fold in egg white beaten with 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour into 9-inch cake pan lined with greased wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pan or 10 minutes before removing to wire rack to cool completely.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and milk, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until well blended.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: peanut butter mini-wheats
directions: Mix crushed Mini Wheats, peanut butter, sugar, flour, butter and salt.
Stir in water slowly; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon flour if needed.
Spoon drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: avocado dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Chill; serve with corn chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: party pizzas
directions: After browning meat and draining, add cheese to melt.
Mix. Add spices and at last Worcestershire sauce.
Chill before spreading on bread.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve hot.
(May also freeze.)

title: hungarian torte cake
directions: Separate eggs. Beat whites separately until stiff.
Beat sugar and yolks until fluffy.
Add flour and baking powder.
Fold in by hand the walnuts (pecans) and vanilla.
Add to egg whites and fold.
Grease 3 round cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Allow to cool.
Ice with a good chocolate icing between layers.

title: quick calzones
directions: Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, Prosciutto, basil and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Brush 2 large baking sheets with salad oil; set aside.
Divide each loaf into 3 equal parts.
Roll each piece into a 7-inch round.
On half of each round, place 1/2 cup cheese mixture.
Spread to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Beat eggs with 1 tablespoon water; brush over edges of dough round fold.
Pinch edges to seal.
Place 3 calzones on each baking sheet.
Brush calzones with salad oil. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
Servings: 6.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Mix Butter Buds and brown sugar substitute. Serve.

title: baby food bars
directions: Mix together and pour in jellyroll pan; bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: glazed carrot coins
directions: In a food processor, with the slicing blade, cut the carrots into thin slices.
In a medium sauce pan, bring the apple juice, butter and brown sugar to a boil over medium-high heat.
Stir in the salt.
Add the carrots, reduce the heat to medium.
Cover and simmer, stirring often until tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cook the carrots uncovered for the last minute or so to reduce the cooking liquid to a glaze.
Toss the carrots with the parsley.
Serve.

title: football game chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Add onion and garlic salt.
Drain grease.
Add salt, oregano and Tabasco sauce.
Break up tomatoes and add along with kidney beans. Mix well and bring to simmer.
Taste for seasonings and correct if needed.
Simmer, covered, for 1 to 2 hours.
If mixture is too thick, add tomato juice.
When serving, sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top, if desired.

title: melt in the mouth cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light. Add sifted flour and other dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cool for 1/2 minute and remove to wire racks.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: tater tot casserole (1)
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, then drain.
Mix beef & onion with all other ingredients.
Put into 9 X 13 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turn temperature down to 325 and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add sugar, vanilla, eggs and margarine.
Put in casserole dish, then mix together brown sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over potatoes.
Top with pecans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: honeymoon pork chops
directions: Have freshly cut 3/4-inch to 1-inch pork chops.
Use onion salt on both sides, then flour.
Place in Pyrex baking dish to fit chops close together.
Cover with hot milk to slightly cover chops.
If desired, use a little pepper and parsley.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.
(More chops may take longer.)
They are done when milk is gone and tops are lightly brown.
Keeps well in low oven for 1/2 hour.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season pork chops
with salt and pepper. Dip in beaten egg and then cornflake crumbs. Bake in lightly greased pan at 350 for 45 - 50 minutes or until done.

title: chicken curry
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 7 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove chicken and stir in 1 cup plain yogurt.
Blend well.
Remove 1/4 cup of mixture, blend in 2 tablespoons flour and return to cooker.
Add chicken back in and simmer to thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: millionaire's fudge(russell stover's five pound fudge)
directions: Break up candy in a large bowl and add chocolate chips, nuts and marshmallow cream; mix and set aside.
In a 4-quart pan, mix sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to a hard boil, stirring often to prevent burning.
Reduce heat and boil until soft ball stage is reached.
Test by dropping a bit of mixture into cold water. Boiling time is approximately 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate ingredients and stir until bars and chips are melted and blended.
Pour mixture into 2 or 3 buttered platters, cookie sheets or oblong pans.
Cool and cut into squares.
Store in freezer.

title: spring vegetable casserole
directions: Cut unpeeled potatoes into quarters.
Cut each carrot lengthwise in half, then crosswise into 2-inch pieces.
In 2-quart casserole, cook potatoes, carrots, margarine or butter, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons water, covered, on High for 10 to 14 minutes, until tender.
Stir twice during cooking.

title: broccoli summer salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Toss everything together.
Mix last 3 ingredients together for dressing. Pour over salad.
Serve chilled.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13 dish. Sprinkle the remainder over the top.

title: pineapple ritz
directions: Spray bottom of a 9 x 12 pan with cooking spray.
Place pineapple chunks evenly over the bottom.
Sprinkle sugar and flour over chunks.
Top with crackers, then pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Remove and add cheese.
Return to oven for 10 more minutes until cheese is well melted.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted boiling water for 6 to 8 minutes. Drain in colander.
Return macaroni to saucepan and add Cheez Whiz, margarine, milk and pepper.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Pour into greased 4-quart baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Dot with extra margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: easy apple butter
directions: Put on hose as usual, then put on your rubber kitchen gloves. You can move your pantyhose around on your legs until they feel comfortable.
Really works wonders!!!

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine pineapple juice and water to make 1 cup.
Mix juice with cornstarch, vinegar, brown sugar and soy sauce in pan.
Cook until thickened and clear.
Add meat, pineapple chunks and green pepper.
Simmer on lowest heat for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Good for pork loin roast (cut into bite sized pieces and browned) small meat loaf patties or chicken (boiled and deboned).

title: velveeta fudge(rich dessert)
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Put cocoa and powdered sugar in a large bowl.
Pour cheese and butter over cocoa and sugar.
Stir with a wooden spoon until mixture is blended.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Pour on cookie sheet(s) to cool.

title: low calorie brown bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk.
Stir to blend well. Stir in milk.
Scrape batter out of bowl and pile in middle of nonstick cookie sheet.
Rub hands with oil so batter won't stick; pat and shape into round loaf.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into small meatballs and gently put one at a time into sauce.
Do not mix for first 1/2 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and vanilla.
Add chips and nuts then stir in flour.
Pinch off in balls and press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes about 3-1/2 dozen.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, with electric mixer, cream the Ricotta cheese and cream cheese.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix well.
Add flour and cornstarch, then add the melted butter.
Fold in sour cream.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cut carrots in thick slices.
Combine all ingredients in covered saucepan.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Uncover saucepan and cook until heavy syrup is formed. Be careful not to burn.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add all other ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in an 8 x 10-inch lightly greased pan for 45 minutes at 350° until firm.
Great for a crowd.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix pudding in 3 cups milk; set aside.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Seed and rinse chilies.
Spread 1/2 of the chilies in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put
Cheddar
cheese
on top.
Layer the rest of the chilies and then the Jack cheese on top.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix
the
remaining
ingredients
and fold into stiff egg whites.
Pour
over
chili
and
cheese in baking dish.
Bake at 325°
for 45 minutes.
Great for brunches.

title: fried turkey
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs.
Beat eggs with fork.
Cut turkey breast into small pieces (not too small).
Dip turkey into egg and roll in crackers.
Drop into hot oil until golden brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Remove from oil and place on rack in roaster. Mix Kitchen Bouquet and water.
Pour half mixture slowly over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Pour rest of water and Kitchen Bouquet over meat after 3/4 hour of baking.

title: apple cider jelly
directions: Prepare glasses and lids and melt paraffin.
In large saucepan or Dutch oven, mix apple cider and fruit pectin well.
Heat mixture over high heat, stirring constantly, until rapidly boiling.
Stir in sugar; boil again 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight. Prepare soup stock by simmering ham in 3 quarts of water for about 2 hours.

Add beans, celery salt, salt, pepper and Accent. Add minced onion and simmer until soup begins to thicken. Add ground ham; sprinkle each portion with parsley flakes and serve with Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add rice, onion, celery, green pepper, sugar, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil and cover. Simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tootie fruity cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
While cake is cooking, combine sugar and pineapple and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.
When cake is done, pour pineapple mixture over top of cake.
Cool completely.
Mix pudding according to directions and pour over pineapple mixture.
Add Cool Whip then coconut.
Decorate with cherries.
Chill until ready to serve. (Can be frozen.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Add the onion and Miracle Whip.
Then slice the cheese and spread through the mixture.
Fry the bacon real crisp.
Drain.
Crumble on top of the casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You can put the olives on top, if desired.
Season to taste.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Mix butter, parsley and thyme.
Do not unroll dough.
Slice dough in 1/2 inch sections as it comes from package.
Spread butter mixture on jelly roll pan and place the dough slices on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with seeds.
Let stand one hour.
Bake as package directs.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and place in large bowl or 9 x 12-inch dish.
Layer eggs, vegetables and bacon in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over top.
Do not stir. Top with grated cheese and cover.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: banana coffee bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar till fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Stir in bananas, and add dry ingredients to butter and mix well.
Pour into greased 9x13 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning and enough water to moisten.
Cook for 15 minutes; cool.
Mix lettuce, avocados, tomatoes, Velveeta cheese, onion and chips.
Mix in cooled meat mixture.
Pour Catalina dressing over salad and mix.
Serve cold.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine all ingredients except for beets.
Add beets and simmer until done.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Mix lightly all
ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, rum, water, salad oil and eggs. Beat 2 to 4 minutes at medium speed.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over bottom.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir together and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: speedy spinach lasagna
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 60 minutes.

title: ginger ball snaps
directions: Roll into balls and dip in sugar.
Place on sheet pan but do not press down.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange ball
directions: Thaw the orange juice and mix with remaining ingredients, except coconut. Chill. Form into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: red hot drink
directions: Dissolve red hots in orange juice.
Add other juices.
Heat, do not boil.
Put in refrigerator between uses.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add pineapple, peaches, nuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.

title: refrigerated butterscotch cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda, cream of tartar and salt. Place shortening and sugar in mixing bowl and cream until light and fluffy.
Add whole eggs and vanilla.
Continue beating and add flour to mixture and mix until well blended; add nuts.
Mold dough into oblong log and chill.
Slice for baking.
May be kept wrapped in wax paper in refrigerator and slice when needed.
Keeps for days.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups of boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add drained pineapple to jello mixture.
Put half of jello mixture into 6 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Let set.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Mix milk, eggs and oil until smooth.
Blend in the pancake mix and add chocolate chips.
Cool on hot lightly greased griddle or waffle iron.
Top with heavy whipping cream, butter or syrup.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend well or with mixer.
Put in greased pie pan (no crust). Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions; cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork and pour mixture of 1 teaspoon sugar and 4 tablespoons of leftover black coffee over brownies; set aside.

title: joe's lasagna
directions: In a medium size, non-stick skillet (I think you need large size), saute ground meat and onion until onion is tender and meat browned.
Do not add fat or oil to skillet (you'll need a little with ground turkey).
Add tomato sauce, basil, parsley, oregano, garlic, pepper and mushrooms to ground meat mixture.
Combine well-drained spinach with cottage cheese.
Cook 1/2 pound noodles in boiling water until tender and drain.
Lightly oil a 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange in layers, beginning with half of the noodles on the bottom.
Spread a layer of the spinach mixture, then the meat sauce and some of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers ending with cheese on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli flowerets, seeds, raisins and red onion with crumbled bacon.
Mix well with dressing.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: southern style dumplings
directions: Make well in center of bowl of flour.
Add salt and pepper. Pour boiling broth from hen into flour stirring all the time with a fork until you have as much as you want.
Turn out onto floured board (I use a big paper sack) and roll out pretty thin.
Cut to desired size and drop into boiling broth a few at a time and cook until done.
Add deboned cooked chicken.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions, saving juice.
Combine juice and other ingredients.
Boil 30 minutes.
Pack into sterilized pint jars.
Seal at once.
Needs to be hot when put in jars.

title: chicken and artichoke mushroom delight
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with salt, pepper and paprika and brown in skillet with 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove chicken to casserole. Arrange the artichokes around the chicken breasts.

title: broccoli-lima bean casserole(serves 12)
directions: Cook broccoli and beans according to directions, no seasoning. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in the order given.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together syrup and sugar.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla, blend well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon soda and stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cold cookie sheet.
Let cool, break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: oven rice
directions: Combine all in covered dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in soup kettle and saute onion until limp.
Add potatoes and water to kettle, season with salt and pepper, and bring to a boil.
Simmer over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 30-40 minutes.
Add corn and cream.
Heat, stirring frequently, for 10 minutes.

title: white cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in layers in medium oven.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in mixing bowl.
Blend; add coconut, pineapple, butter, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except apples and raisins, then add apples and raisins.
Stir just to mix.
If mixture is too dry, add a little orange juice.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy-quick dump cake
directions: Spread all in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: he-man spanish rice
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper, salt, chili powder and garlic powder in skillet until beef is brown and crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook 30 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring often.

title: cream puffs
directions: Blend drained pineapple, whipped topping and cream cheese at low speed until creamy. Slice cookies in half on cookie sheet. Spread mixture on each half and place tops on.
Refrigerate until served.

title: cocktail franks
directions: Mix ingredients and franks.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes and serve.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; add egg.
Beat thoroughly and add rhubarb.
Line pie pan with pastry and pour in filling.
Cover with top crust or lattice and bake in a very hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to moderate (350°) and bake 35 minutes longer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain.
Add oleo, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, onion, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for 40 minutes (uncovered).

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cover soup bones and meat with water.
Add celery and onions and carrots.
Boil about 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients. Return to a boil then simmer until potatoes are done, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carciofi-fritti(fried artichokes)
directions: Sprinkle hearts with salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Mix parsley, oregano and basil with bread crumb mixture.
Beat eggs slightly.
Dip hearts in egg and roll in bread crumb mixture.
Fry in hot oil, about 3 minutes, on each side or until golden brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: old time egg custard
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into deep pie shell.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and
juice
of lemons in double boiler until thick.
Cool
in
refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, mix pineapple, pecans,	fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Whip cream and mix all together.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese, add red pepper. Work butter in and work flour in. Blending well. Put on floured boards and roll about 1/2 inch thick, press down with fork, cut in strips and cook in hot over, 425° about 10 minutes or until golden brown. If these are packed in air-tight container they will keep for weeks.

title: african chicken
directions: Rub chicken with Tabasco sauce.
Roll in flour.
Lightly brown in hot oil.
Put into baking dish.
Saute onion in browning pan. Add oil if necessary.
Add all other ingredients to pan.
Stir until hot and bubbly.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or cook in covered electric frypan.
Serve with brown rice or mashed potatoes.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Grease 1 qt baking dish.
Arrange half of apples on bottom. Follow with half bread then half sugar.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Cut margarine in pieces and lay on top.
Pour hot water over all.
Bake covered at 350 F for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake another 10 minutes.

title: perfect custard pie
directions: Warm milk slightly and add all other ingredients.
Beat together in electric mixer or blender until well mixed.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell which has been thoroughly chilled (Pyrex is best).
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soak onion soup in hot water for 1/2 hour.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Blend mixture into cream cheese and beat to make smooth paste.
Add milk and mix well.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: easy egg sandwich
directions: Beat eggs and milk in microwavable bowl.
Cook in microwave for 40 seconds on high power.
Stir briskly.
Return to microwave for 40 seconds more or until egg is fluffy.
Place slice of cheese on eggs while still warm and add to toast.

title: pot roast
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven, put in 2 tablespoons hot oil.
Brown roast on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 2 hours, stirring often.
Add vegetables; cover.
Cook 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are tender.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: In medium saucepan, Do Not use any oil or butter, season shrimp with Cavender's seasoning, add garlic, and cook until shrimp are done.
Add heavy cream and cheese until all melted together, then add pasta until desired amount and consistency achieved.

title: donut
directions: Melt yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Add flour and mix well with a wooden spoon.
Cover and let set 1/2 hour.
Add salt and let set until double in bulk.
Batter will be soft and sticky.
Drop batter by tablespoon in hot fat at 350°.
Brown on all sides. Drain on paper towels.
Dust with 10x sugar.

title: loaded mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Place in a Dutch oven; cover with water.
Boil until tender.
Drain and place in a very large bowl (or back in Dutch oven).
Add sour cream, milk, butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Beat on medium-low speed until light and fluffy. Stir in 2 cups cheese, the bacon and green onions.
Transfer to a greased 3-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Serves 14.

title: magic fruit cake balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, cut into small squares and empty onto a tea towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix altogether and place in mold or glass bowl and refrigerate until set.

title: tuna or salmon things
directions: Drain fish, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Put fish into bowl, break apart.
Add flour and slightly beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add baking powder to liquid, beat with a fork until foamy.
Pour into fish mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil until brown.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Separate rolls.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on rolls.
Cut each into thirds and roll up.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Wash, slice and cook mushrooms slightly (5 minutes).
Drain.
Melt butter in water.
Combine with stuffing mix.
Layer mushrooms, cheese and then stuffing in a 13 x 9-inch buttered casserole dish.
Repeat, ending with stuffing. Dot with butter.
Just before cooking, pour over half and half.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover; let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Separate into containers and freeze.
Sugar won't dissolve.

title: slaw
directions: Mix well; toss lightly.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.

title: ham dip
directions: Place all ingredients in mixer bowl and mix until creamy. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Drop unpeeled garlic cloves into boiling water for 1 minute (30 seconds for small cloves); remove from water, peel and mince.
Cut broccoli into buds and steams, discarding woody portions and cook in boiling water until tender.
Remove and drain.
Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
When butter begins to bubble, add garlic, stirring rapidly for a few seconds.
Quickly add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly for 1 minute.
Add milk and chicken broth, stirring briskly with a wire whisk until sauce is thickened.
In a blender or food processor, puree broccoli with a little sauce, adding remaining sauce until all broccoli is blended.
Correct seasoning to taste and thin with half and half to proper consistency.
Serve, sprinkled with Hungarian sweet paprika, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus and mushroom vinaigrette
directions: In large skillet in small amount of boiling water, cook asparagus for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange asparagus and mushrooms in shallow dish.
In small jar, place remaining ingredients.
Cover and shake well.
Pour over asparagus.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy does it eggless chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a medium bowl. Add remaining ingredients, and stir well.

title: pecan cookie
directions: Put wax paper on bottom of cookie sheet.
Beat egg yolks (yellow part of egg) with sugar and vanilla until white, then add chopped pecans in mix.
With a teaspoon, place mix on cookie sheet that is covered with wax paper (3-inch standard size cookie).
Set oven to 300°.
Bake for 20 minutes.
(Cookies should look white.)

title: granddaddy's chili
directions: Cook bacon and lay on paper towel to drain.
Add onion, celery, pepper and garlic to bacon grease.
Just before it browns, add the ground beef.
Turn up heat to brown meat, stirring to keep from burning it.
After meat browns, add tomatoes, kidney beans, chili powder, salt, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cut down heat to barely bubbling and cook a long time (3 to 6 hours).
Stir occasionally.
Break up bacon and put in chili; add black pepper.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Make 1 envelope Dream Whip and beat into sugar and cream cheese.
Place in crust.
Top with second envelope of Dream Whip, then top with cherry filling. Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: broccoli bakeroswell, new mexico
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook broccoli as directed until just heated through.
Drain.
Mix broccoli and Velveeta.
Spoon into greased 10 X 6 baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs, dot with margarine.
Bake 25-30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: beef casserole
directions: Trim steak and cut into bite sized pieces.
Combine all ingredients.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all in bowl.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Can keep several days in refrigerator. Frost with buttercream or cream cheese frosting.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Mix the evaporated milk and ground beef.
Mix the stuffing according to package.
Divide beef into 5 parts. Pat each into a 6-inch circle on wax paper.
Put approximately 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each and draw meat up over stuffing.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Mix soup, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup together and spoon over each bundle.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and thighs in salted water.
Save the broth.
Pick off chicken and put in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Saute an onion in butter.
Prepare stuffing as directed, using broth instead of water to make moist.
Mix milk and cream of chicken soup.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Next, place stuffing on top and pour broth over to keep moist.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° to heat thoroughly.
Excellent to make a day ahead of time.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg substitute and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Top each serving with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and/or chocolate shavings.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal with water and allow to stand 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Stir until blended, not longer.
Place in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter may be stored, covered, in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: quick and easy chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl combine chocolate, butter and water.
Stir until chocolate is melted and mix is smooth.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Beat on low until smooth.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Frost as desired and serve.

title: goo-losh
directions: Cook the macaroni in one pan; boil..
Cook the ground chuck, onions and green pepper together and drain.
Then put tomato juice and tomatoes in and add all together.
Salt and pepper.
Cook for half an hour.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cut chicken breasts into large pieces.	Use a casserole dish. Cover with cream
of
chicken
mushroom soup.
Sprinkle (dry) stuffing mix over the top.	Bake
minutes at 350° or until tender.

title: baked squash puff
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole; set aside. Combine all ingredients in medium bowl; blend well.
Spoon into prepared casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes, or until lightly browned and heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly; stir in sugar, syrup and butter.
Add pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: salad supreme
directions: Wash and chop raw vegetables as desired.
Place in bowl with water chestnuts and eggs.
In blender, mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate. Serve with rolls or crackers.

title: polish babka
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm milk, 1 ounce of sugar and a little flour; set in warm place until it rises to top of cup.
Sift flour in large mixing bowl and make a well in middle.
Put yeast mixture into this well together with remaining 3 1/2 ounces of sugar, dash of salt and 2 eggs.
Knead dough well, adding as much of remaining warm milk as flour will absorb.
Add 3 1/2 ounces melted butter, lemon rind and raisins and knead a little more, then place dough in floured bowl.
Cover with thin cloth and allow to rise in warm place until double in bulk.

title: baked chicken
directions: Take skin off chicken; rinse and roll in bread crumbs. Place on a cookie sheet covered with foil. Spray chicken with Pam and shake seasoned salt on chicken. Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Layer one box of ice cream sandwiches in a long pan and cover with cool whip. Add second box of ice cream sandwiches and cover with remaining cool whip.
You can put nuts on top.
Keep in freezer.
